1
00:00:06,734 --> 00:00:10,577
[In The Space Of A Week
Spring Has Come To The Village]

2
00:00:10,577 --> 00:00:15,267
[Is The Bakery Open?]

3
00:00:17,351 --> 00:00:21,254
[Are They Open Yet?]

4
00:00:21,855 --> 00:00:26,726
[They Wait With Affectionate Expectation]

5
00:00:28,629 --> 00:00:30,430
[After A Week-Long Wait]

6
00:00:30,430 --> 00:00:33,567
[Bonjour Bakery Is Open Again!]

7
00:00:33,567 --> 00:00:37,938
[Bonjour Bakery]

8
00:00:37,938 --> 00:00:41,241
[Ki Taek Arrives First]

9
00:00:47,548 --> 00:00:51,017
[He Gets Straight Into His Uniform
And Heads To The Kitchen]

10
00:00:53,820 --> 00:00:57,257
[He Quickly Looks Up A Recipe]

11
00:00:59,459 --> 00:01:03,564
[Does He Need To Get Ingredients Ready
Before Chef Cha Arrives?]

12
00:01:03,564 --> 00:01:07,334
[Let's Get Started]
Okay, let's do this.

13
00:01:12,372 --> 00:01:16,943
[Oh, He's Boiling Eggs]

14
00:01:21,648 --> 00:01:24,084
Oh, no! It cracked.

15
00:01:24,851 --> 00:01:27,888
[Crestfallen]

16
00:01:27,888 --> 00:01:30,891
[Let's Cover It Up
With One That Isn't Cracked]

17
00:01:32,059 --> 00:01:34,027
It's so soft.

18
00:01:36,496 --> 00:01:39,700
[Let's Try The Bread First]

19
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:42,002
I heard Anseong is known
for its local breads.

20
00:01:42,970 --> 00:01:45,038
I see why it's so good. It's made of rice.

21
00:01:45,038 --> 00:01:48,508
[Filling Up On Anseong Chiffon Cake
Made Of Locally Grown Rice]

22
00:01:52,980 --> 00:01:53,880
[Before The Bakery Opens]

23
00:01:53,880 --> 00:01:55,349
[A Polite Young Man Arrives]
Good morning.

24
00:01:55,349 --> 00:01:57,818
Hello.

25
00:01:57,818 --> 00:02:01,054
[I Haven't Seen You Before]

26
00:02:01,054 --> 00:02:04,858
All right.

27
00:02:06,493 --> 00:02:10,230
[He Looks Very Nervous]
Okay.

28
00:02:10,230 --> 00:02:12,532
Let's try them both at once.

29
00:02:14,201 --> 00:02:18,738
[He Jumps Right In To Making Coffee
Without Hesitation]

30
00:02:20,674 --> 00:02:24,411
[Who Is This Young Man?]

31
00:02:26,780 --> 00:02:28,148
[An All-Round Talent]

32
00:02:28,148 --> 00:02:31,718
[From The Group Wanna One
The Viewing Public's Top Pick]

33
00:02:32,285 --> 00:02:35,889
[Icon Of The Young Generation
Starring In Movies, Dramas, Musicals]

34
00:02:35,889 --> 00:02:39,326
[New Staff Member Ong Seong Wu]

35
00:02:39,326 --> 00:02:40,894
- Hello.
- Hello.

36
00:02:40,894 --> 00:02:43,130
[Day Before The Opening]
I feel so guilty.

37
00:02:43,130 --> 00:02:45,465
I can't believe you came all this way.

38
00:02:45,465 --> 00:02:49,302
[They Met In Advance For Pre-Training]
Thank you. What am I going to do?

39
00:02:50,737 --> 00:02:51,872
I'm sorry.

40
00:02:51,872 --> 00:02:54,007
I have to perform tomorrow.

41
00:02:54,007 --> 00:02:57,110
[With His Play Pre-Booked]
You would have to cover me for a day.

42
00:02:57,110 --> 00:02:58,178
[Seon Ho Will Be Away]

43
00:02:58,178 --> 00:02:59,546
With such an elite recruit.

44
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:02,082
- You're in for a rough ride.
- I'm worried.

45
00:03:02,082 --> 00:03:03,083
[Seong Wu Must Fill In]
Oh, man.

46
00:03:03,083 --> 00:03:05,452
- But from what I hear,
- Yes?

47
00:03:05,452 --> 00:03:06,653
- Well...
- you're experienced.

48
00:03:06,653 --> 00:03:09,589
[It Was For A Drama]
I played a part-timer in a café once.

49
00:03:09,589 --> 00:03:12,092
It was a series called
<i>Would You Like a Cup of Coffee?</i>

50
00:03:12,092 --> 00:03:13,026
[He Learned It For The Role]
<i>But...</i>

51
00:03:13,026 --> 00:03:14,127
Tomorrow's our first weekend.

52
00:03:14,127 --> 00:03:16,029
[As They Face Their First Weekend]
We've never opened on a weekend before.

53
00:03:16,029 --> 00:03:19,700
[They Need To Be Prepared]
Now that word is out about the bakery...

54
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:20,767
Check that it's level.

55
00:03:20,767 --> 00:03:23,670
Yes, you don't need to tap too hard.

56
00:03:23,670 --> 00:03:26,606
[So The Changeover Begins]

57
00:03:28,709 --> 00:03:30,544
- When a customer comes in,
- Yes.

58
00:03:30,544 --> 00:03:32,746
- say "Welcome!"
- "Welcome!"

59
00:03:32,746 --> 00:03:34,915
Only seniors over 65 years old can enter.

60
00:03:34,915 --> 00:03:36,249
"Only those over 65 years old can enter."

61
00:03:36,249 --> 00:03:37,718
- So you need to check ID...
- Yes.

62
00:03:37,718 --> 00:03:40,253
- You don't need to repeat what I say.
- Okay.

63
00:03:41,221 --> 00:03:43,356
- Here we go.
- Okay.

64
00:03:46,293 --> 00:03:49,096
- These two are for making ades?
- That's right.

65
00:03:49,096 --> 00:03:50,563
[The Training Lasted Into The Evening]

66
00:03:54,301 --> 00:03:55,635
- Hello.
- You're here.

67
00:03:55,635 --> 00:03:56,870
- Yes, did you sleep well?
- I did.

68
00:03:56,870 --> 00:03:58,305
- Did you sleep well?
- Yes.

69
00:03:58,305 --> 00:04:00,240
By the way, do you eat...

70
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:03,176
- Do you eat eggs and stuff for breakfast?
- Yes?

71
00:04:03,176 --> 00:04:05,512
- Do you eat eggs and stuff for breakfast?
- Yes?

72
00:04:05,512 --> 00:04:07,047
- Absolutely.
- Really?

73
00:04:07,047 --> 00:04:09,583
I mean, it's nothing special.

74
00:04:09,583 --> 00:04:11,818
- I usually boil some eggs
- Okay.

75
00:04:11,818 --> 00:04:14,321
and make a smoothie with black beans,
blueberries, and tomatoes.

76
00:04:14,321 --> 00:04:16,656
- I see.
- Would you like to try some?

77
00:04:16,656 --> 00:04:18,391
- Yes, please.
- You'd like that?

78
00:04:18,391 --> 00:04:20,827
- Yes.
- All right, then.

79
00:04:21,394 --> 00:04:23,497
- Good luck today.
- Let's do this.

80
00:04:23,497 --> 00:04:24,731
I hear you're good at everything.

81
00:04:24,731 --> 00:04:26,299
- You're an all-round talent.
- No.

82
00:04:26,299 --> 00:04:28,535
- I'm sure you'll do great.
- I don't know.

83
00:04:30,704 --> 00:04:34,074
[People Say The Korean Azalea
Symbolizes The Joy Of Love]

84
00:04:39,746 --> 00:04:41,714
The King of Baking!

85
00:04:42,983 --> 00:04:44,451
I'm heading in.

86
00:04:50,991 --> 00:04:53,126
The King of Baking.

87
00:04:53,126 --> 00:04:56,163
[Are You Okay?]

88
00:04:56,163 --> 00:04:59,065
[The King Of Baking Heads Into Work]

89
00:05:01,201 --> 00:05:03,269
- Hey.
- Hello.

90
00:05:03,970 --> 00:05:05,705
You're dressed smartly.

91
00:05:05,705 --> 00:05:07,707
- What are you doing? Cleaning?
- Yes, I'm cleaning.

92
00:05:07,707 --> 00:05:09,909
[Seung Won Featured
In A Wanna One Music Video 9 Years Ago]

93
00:05:12,345 --> 00:05:15,315
The King of Baking!

94
00:05:16,183 --> 00:05:18,585
I know everything about baking.

95
00:05:22,823 --> 00:05:23,957
Today...

96
00:05:23,957 --> 00:05:25,925
[The King Of Baking's Morning Routine]

97
00:05:27,627 --> 00:05:31,197
[Checking Today's Menu]
We have another insane line-up today.

98
00:05:31,998 --> 00:05:35,602
[He Changes Into His Uniform]

99
00:05:39,206 --> 00:05:42,308
[Bandana On, Ready For Action]

100
00:05:45,078 --> 00:05:48,915
I'm ready to go!

101
00:05:51,117 --> 00:05:52,786
[Actually, He's Not Done Yet]

102
00:05:52,786 --> 00:05:55,555
The King of Baking.

103
00:05:55,555 --> 00:05:58,024
The pinnacle of baking.

104
00:05:58,024 --> 00:06:00,160
The mecca of baking.

105
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:02,462
[Does He Want Boiled Eggs?]

106
00:06:02,462 --> 00:06:05,431
Welcome to Bonjour Bakery.

107
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:09,936
[Acting Borderline Crazy]

108
00:06:09,936 --> 00:06:11,838
I'm feeling good today.

109
00:06:15,242 --> 00:06:17,677
All right. Come on.

110
00:06:17,677 --> 00:06:20,614
- Let's give it our all.
- Yes, Seung Won.

111
00:06:20,614 --> 00:06:24,417
Ki Taek and I suddenly bonded yesterday.

112
00:06:25,719 --> 00:06:27,787
Up until yesterday,

113
00:06:27,787 --> 00:06:29,723
the emotional distance was 30 meters,

114
00:06:29,723 --> 00:06:32,726
but now it's 15 meters.

115
00:06:32,726 --> 00:06:34,961
It came down pretty fast.

116
00:06:34,961 --> 00:06:37,197
We might end up like this someday.

117
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:42,135
- It got way too close.
- Yes, it did.

118
00:06:42,135 --> 00:06:45,572
[While The Kitchen Team Bonds]

119
00:06:54,214 --> 00:06:57,684
[The New Part-Timer Moves About Restlessly]

120
00:06:58,318 --> 00:07:00,387
[He Scans The Bakery Like A Robot]

121
00:07:00,387 --> 00:07:02,155
What should I...

122
00:07:03,290 --> 00:07:05,292
What should I...

123
00:07:05,292 --> 00:07:07,460
What should I be doing?

124
00:07:07,460 --> 00:07:09,863
- This is the first thing you should do.
- Okay.

125
00:07:09,863 --> 00:07:10,797
[Loading Morning Protocol 1]

126
00:07:10,797 --> 00:07:13,099
You need to do a quick sweep of the hall.

127
00:07:13,867 --> 00:07:17,070
[Running Through Seon Ho's Instructions]

128
00:07:18,004 --> 00:07:21,574
[Protocol 1]
[Clean The Hall First And Foremost]

129
00:07:26,112 --> 00:07:27,180
There's a blackboard.

130
00:07:27,180 --> 00:07:31,084
[Loading Morning Protocol 2]
You need to write out the menu of the day.

131
00:07:32,052 --> 00:07:36,756
[Protocol 2]
[Write Out The Menu In Nice Handwriting]

132
00:07:40,393 --> 00:07:43,196
[A Slight Fail On The Handwriting]

133
00:07:44,030 --> 00:07:46,933
[Bonjour Cherry Blossom Tart]

134
00:07:47,534 --> 00:07:48,902
[Before The Spring Rain Falls]

135
00:07:48,902 --> 00:07:53,273
[There Is One Thing We Must Do]

136
00:07:55,642 --> 00:07:59,546
[We Need To Enjoy The Cherry Blossoms]

137
00:07:59,546 --> 00:08:02,148
[While They Are Still In Bloom]

138
00:08:03,316 --> 00:08:07,120
[Before You Can Catch A Whiff
Of The Fragrant Petals]

139
00:08:08,154 --> 00:08:12,191
[Spring Passes By All Too Quickly]

140
00:08:12,859 --> 00:08:16,562
[Bonjour Bakery Came Up With An Idea]

141
00:08:18,298 --> 00:08:19,799
[Can We Capture]

142
00:08:19,799 --> 00:08:23,403
[A Fleeting Moment Of Spring In A Dish?]

143
00:08:24,237 --> 00:08:26,939
[Introducing A Dessert
Infused With The Spirit Of Spring]

144
00:08:27,507 --> 00:08:30,844
[Bonjour Cherry Blossom Tart]

145
00:08:30,844 --> 00:08:31,978
Bonjour.

146
00:08:31,978 --> 00:08:33,013
- Cherry Blossom!
- Cherry Blossom!

147
00:08:33,013 --> 00:08:34,080
- Tart!
- Tart!

148
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:36,783
[Bonjour Cherry Blossom Tart]
Tart!

149
00:08:36,783 --> 00:08:39,285
Is that right?

150
00:08:39,285 --> 00:08:42,789
[That's Right!]
[Coming Up Soon!]

151
00:08:43,456 --> 00:08:48,261
[Manager Hee Ae Arrives At Work
Along With The Spring Breeze]

152
00:08:54,501 --> 00:08:55,968
Good morning, Hee Ae.

153
00:08:56,636 --> 00:08:58,571
Good morning.

154
00:08:58,571 --> 00:09:00,340
It's so nice to meet you.

155
00:09:00,340 --> 00:09:02,242
It's a pleasure to meet you.

156
00:09:02,242 --> 00:09:03,943
I'm Ong Seong Wu.

157
00:09:04,878 --> 00:09:08,047
I heard you're experienced.

158
00:09:09,149 --> 00:09:10,950
You've been misinformed.

159
00:09:10,950 --> 00:09:11,951
- Is that right?
- Yes.

160
00:09:11,951 --> 00:09:13,787
But I trained hard yesterday.

161
00:09:13,787 --> 00:09:15,055
- Really?
- Yes.

162
00:09:15,055 --> 00:09:16,322
In that case,

163
00:09:16,322 --> 00:09:19,726
- could you make me a decaf latte?
- Sure.

164
00:09:19,726 --> 00:09:21,061
- A decaf latte?
- Yes.

165
00:09:21,061 --> 00:09:23,196
- Do you want it hot?
- Yes, please.

166
00:09:23,196 --> 00:09:24,497
[While Seong Wu Takes His First Order]
Thank you.

167
00:09:24,497 --> 00:09:26,166
[Flowers Bloom In The Kitchen]
Take it off when it starts to boil.

168
00:09:26,166 --> 00:09:27,300
Okay.

169
00:09:27,901 --> 00:09:29,369
- Now.
- Okay.

170
00:09:29,369 --> 00:09:30,770
- All right.
- I'll leave it to cool.

171
00:09:30,770 --> 00:09:32,205
[Start By Making Peach Sauce]
Let it cool.

172
00:09:32,205 --> 00:09:33,773
- It smells so good.
- Right?

173
00:09:33,773 --> 00:09:35,041
I love the smell of peach.

174
00:09:35,041 --> 00:09:36,976
It's so nice.

175
00:09:36,976 --> 00:09:39,779
[The Sauce That Is Boiled Then Cooled
Is Called A Coulis]

176
00:09:43,850 --> 00:09:47,453
[While Chef Cha Half-Fills Round Molds
With The Coulis]

177
00:09:48,188 --> 00:09:50,557
[Ki Taek Portions Out 7g Of Lychee]

178
00:09:50,557 --> 00:09:52,558
Seven grams, right? Let's see.

179
00:09:55,195 --> 00:09:57,931
[7g Of Lychee Added]

180
00:09:57,931 --> 00:10:00,867
[Another 7g On Standby]

181
00:10:00,867 --> 00:10:02,902
[Quick Handover]
This is also seven grams.

182
00:10:04,137 --> 00:10:06,038
[Here Is Another 7g]
You're doing great, Ki Taek.

183
00:10:07,006 --> 00:10:08,975
[7,000kg Of Praise For 7g]
I'm impressed.

184
00:10:08,975 --> 00:10:10,576
You're great to work with.

185
00:10:11,177 --> 00:10:12,312
Thank you.

186
00:10:12,312 --> 00:10:14,147
You're doing great.

187
00:10:14,147 --> 00:10:15,448
[Blushing]

188
00:10:15,448 --> 00:10:17,450
Well done.

189
00:10:18,251 --> 00:10:21,254
[Add Another Layer Of Peach Coulis]

190
00:10:21,254 --> 00:10:22,589
- Ki Taek, I need...
- Yes?

191
00:10:22,589 --> 00:10:24,824
- I need one of the... That's it.
- Here.

192
00:10:24,824 --> 00:10:26,526
[He's A Mindreader]
You're the best.

193
00:10:26,526 --> 00:10:27,894
I didn't need to finish my sentence.

194
00:10:27,894 --> 00:10:29,562
He's amazing.

195
00:10:29,562 --> 00:10:31,131
[Freeze It For One Hour]
Move this to the freezer.

196
00:10:31,131 --> 00:10:33,066
- Okay.
- Move it over.

197
00:10:33,066 --> 00:10:36,436
[The Heart Of The Cherry Blossom Tart]

198
00:10:36,436 --> 00:10:39,239
[This Peach Coulis Is Encased]

199
00:10:39,239 --> 00:10:43,009
[In An Orange Blossom Mousse]

200
00:10:43,009 --> 00:10:46,012
[While He Is On A Roll,
Ki Taek Gives It A Go]

201
00:10:46,012 --> 00:10:47,447
[Egg]

202
00:10:47,447 --> 00:10:49,349
[Sugar]

203
00:10:49,349 --> 00:10:50,817
[Milk Tea]
And then...

204
00:10:53,186 --> 00:10:55,421
I'll take it off when it hits 80 degrees.

205
00:10:55,421 --> 00:10:57,223
[Heat The Mixture To 80 Degrees]

206
00:10:57,223 --> 00:10:58,458
- Okay.
- I'll pour it in.

207
00:10:58,458 --> 00:11:00,426
[Ruby Chocolate]
[A Naturally Pink Chocolate]

208
00:11:00,426 --> 00:11:03,129
[It's The 4th Generation Of Chocolate
Alongside Dark, Milk, And White Chocolate]

209
00:11:05,865 --> 00:11:08,601
[Add Some Whipped Cream]

210
00:11:08,601 --> 00:11:11,737
[Then Mix It With A Spatula
To Create The Finished Mousse]

211
00:11:12,539 --> 00:11:14,974
[Choosing The Right Spatula With Great Care]

212
00:11:19,145 --> 00:11:20,880
Isn't that spatula too big?

213
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:22,115
[Is It?]

214
00:11:22,115 --> 00:11:24,184
Did you have to pick that one?

215
00:11:24,184 --> 00:11:25,251
It's a bit too...

216
00:11:25,251 --> 00:11:26,853
Why did you have to go for that one?

217
00:11:26,853 --> 00:11:27,887
- You're right.
- Just look.

218
00:11:27,887 --> 00:11:30,156
- It's way too big.
- Yeah.

219
00:11:30,156 --> 00:11:32,926
Isn't this more like a paddle?

220
00:11:32,926 --> 00:11:36,062
[Balancing Praise With Tough Love]
It's basically a paddle.

221
00:11:36,062 --> 00:11:38,831
[Let's Use The Paddle To Spank Ki Taek]

222
00:11:38,831 --> 00:11:42,168
[Time For Chef Cha To Step Back In]

223
00:11:43,203 --> 00:11:45,771
[There Goes His Poor Back Again]

224
00:11:49,475 --> 00:11:52,845
[Fill 60 Percent Of Each Mold With Coulis]

225
00:12:01,054 --> 00:12:02,789
[Take The Frozen Peach Coulis]

226
00:12:02,789 --> 00:12:04,357
It needs to be placed like this.

227
00:12:05,191 --> 00:12:08,060
[Tuck The Peach Coulis
Inside The Orange Blossom Mousse]

228
00:12:12,966 --> 00:12:16,402
[Satisfied]

229
00:12:17,337 --> 00:12:20,907
[But]

230
00:12:21,841 --> 00:12:26,679
[Capturing The Essence Of Spring
Is No Easy Feat]

231
00:12:31,951 --> 00:12:35,488
[A Rallying Cry To Boost His Energy]

232
00:12:37,357 --> 00:12:40,827
[The Main Ingredient
Of The Cherry Blossom Petal]

233
00:12:40,827 --> 00:12:44,864
[Is A Radish!]

234
00:12:44,864 --> 00:12:47,967
[Radish]
[A Small, Round, Red Root Vegetable]

235
00:12:47,967 --> 00:12:50,036
[Sugar]

236
00:12:51,137 --> 00:12:53,272
[After A Sugar Bath]

237
00:12:54,340 --> 00:12:57,376
[The Fine Veining Of The Petals Emerge]

238
00:12:57,944 --> 00:13:01,347
[The Ruby Chocolate Glaze Is Back]

239
00:13:01,347 --> 00:13:05,651
[This Chocolate Glaze Will Soon Act
As The Glue For The Petals]

240
00:13:18,531 --> 00:13:19,866
Okay.

241
00:13:19,866 --> 00:13:23,302
[Cream To Secure The Shell]

242
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:31,243
[Add A Swirl Of Raspberry Cream
For A Refreshing Tartness]

243
00:13:31,911 --> 00:13:36,949
[While Ki Taek Sorts The Radish By Size]

244
00:13:36,949 --> 00:13:39,018
These are the small ones, right?
Give me the big ones first.

245
00:13:39,018 --> 00:13:41,387
[Sort Into Large, Medium, Small]
Okay, I'll hand you the big ones first.

246
00:13:41,387 --> 00:13:47,259
[The Biggest Petals Go Around The Base]

247
00:13:54,233 --> 00:13:56,069
- Ki Taek, can you get me
- Yes?

248
00:13:56,069 --> 00:13:58,237
the magnifying glass from my bag?

249
00:13:58,237 --> 00:14:02,008
[Time For The Most Meticulous Stage]

250
00:14:02,008 --> 00:14:06,479
[Chef's Vision Has Been Upgraded]

251
00:14:06,479 --> 00:14:09,982
[Use Medium-Sized Petals For The 2nd Layer]

252
00:14:22,795 --> 00:14:24,364
- Okay, it's ready.
- Okay.

253
00:14:24,364 --> 00:14:27,967
[The Cherry Blossom
Is Finally In Full Bloom]

254
00:14:35,174 --> 00:14:38,945
I proudly recommend it.

255
00:14:38,945 --> 00:14:41,080
[Bonjour Bakery]

256
00:14:47,553 --> 00:14:48,888
[You Must Be Over 65 Years Old To Enter]

257
00:14:48,888 --> 00:14:51,057
[Before Opening]
[Bonjour Bakery]

258
00:14:51,791 --> 00:14:54,694
It's too pretty to eat.

259
00:14:55,695 --> 00:14:56,963
- It's a shame.
- Hee Ae.

260
00:14:56,963 --> 00:14:58,064
- Yes?
- Have you seen our tart?

261
00:14:58,064 --> 00:14:59,432
- The Cherry Blossom Tart.
- The Cherry Blossom Tart.

262
00:14:59,432 --> 00:15:01,167
- We...
- I've only seen it in a photo.

263
00:15:01,167 --> 00:15:02,668
[Eager To Show It Off]
We made these today.

264
00:15:02,668 --> 00:15:04,170
- I know.
- We just made them.

265
00:15:04,170 --> 00:15:06,339
[Proud Moment]
Take a look at the finished product.

266
00:15:06,339 --> 00:15:08,741
- Take a look at the finished product.
- Can I taste it?

267
00:15:08,741 --> 00:15:10,843
- Taste it?
- Yes.

268
00:15:10,843 --> 00:15:11,977
Again?

269
00:15:12,678 --> 00:15:15,281
I haven't tasted this one!

270
00:15:15,281 --> 00:15:17,950
- I should taste it as the manager.
- She's right.

271
00:15:17,950 --> 00:15:19,318
[Using The Manager Card]
There you go.

272
00:15:19,886 --> 00:15:21,988
They're freshly baked. Take a look.

273
00:15:21,988 --> 00:15:24,490
- They're gorgeous.
- Right?

274
00:15:24,490 --> 00:15:26,959
It looks like a flower bouquet.

275
00:15:26,959 --> 00:15:28,795
It's so pretty.

276
00:15:28,795 --> 00:15:30,830
[Intro: Never Seen Anything This Pretty]
I've never seen anything like it.

277
00:15:30,830 --> 00:15:32,565
- Isn't it beautiful?
- Yes.

278
00:15:32,565 --> 00:15:35,801
[Main Idea 1: Knife-Cutting ASMR]

279
00:15:37,737 --> 00:15:40,773
[Main Idea 2: A Focused Look]

280
00:15:40,773 --> 00:15:43,476
Let me give it a try.

281
00:15:45,278 --> 00:15:48,247
[Conclusion: One Big Bite]

282
00:15:50,216 --> 00:15:53,119
[How Is It?]

283
00:15:53,119 --> 00:15:54,353
It's so refreshing!

284
00:15:54,353 --> 00:15:55,555
Do you think so?

285
00:15:55,555 --> 00:15:57,890
[Peach, Lychee, Raspberry Combo]
Is it refreshing? Do you like it?

286
00:15:57,890 --> 00:15:59,358
It's tasty.

287
00:15:59,358 --> 00:16:02,094
- Did you make it, Ki Taek?
- You need to put at least two petals.

288
00:16:07,166 --> 00:16:08,734
- It's good, right?
- It's so good.

289
00:16:08,734 --> 00:16:10,036
[The Ong-Droid Can't Help But Smile]

290
00:16:10,036 --> 00:16:11,504
Then we're all set.

291
00:16:11,504 --> 00:16:15,475
[15 Minutes Before Opening]

292
00:16:15,475 --> 00:16:17,810
[Nervous About His First Day]
Hold on.

293
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:18,878
It's just that...

294
00:16:18,878 --> 00:16:22,281
When the customers come in,
since I've never...

295
00:16:22,281 --> 00:16:23,783
[Not Very Confident]
I've never greeted customers before.

296
00:16:23,783 --> 00:16:25,384
[Recalling The Protocol]
Let's do a trial run.

297
00:16:25,384 --> 00:16:29,288
Imagine a customer has walked in.

298
00:16:29,288 --> 00:16:30,823
[Protocol 3]
[Practice When You're Not Sure]

299
00:16:30,823 --> 00:16:32,859
Welcome.

300
00:16:32,859 --> 00:16:34,260
Hello.

301
00:16:34,260 --> 00:16:37,063
[Suddenly?]
You have to be over 65 years old to enter.

302
00:16:37,063 --> 00:16:39,131
Can I see your ID?

303
00:16:39,131 --> 00:16:40,366
I should say "check your ID."

304
00:16:40,366 --> 00:16:43,869
[The Ong-Droid Performs As Programmed]
Do you mind if I check your ID?

305
00:16:49,342 --> 00:16:50,810
Is this right?

306
00:16:50,810 --> 00:16:53,579
[Programmed To Follow The Mask Protocol]

307
00:16:53,579 --> 00:16:55,615
Try turning it over.

308
00:16:55,615 --> 00:16:57,116
Flip the top and bottom.

309
00:17:00,920 --> 00:17:03,623
Oh, this is how you wear it.

310
00:17:03,623 --> 00:17:05,324
It supports the chin.

311
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:09,962
[Ready To Open]

312
00:17:09,962 --> 00:17:13,699
This is today's morning line-up.

313
00:17:13,699 --> 00:17:17,336
My babies.

314
00:17:19,272 --> 00:17:21,574
[His Precious Babies Are Neatly Displayed]

315
00:17:24,210 --> 00:17:27,112
[Once The Kitchen Team
Is Done Arranging The Display]

316
00:17:28,080 --> 00:17:29,582
- Are we open?
- I'll open.

317
00:17:30,216 --> 00:17:33,452
[The Bakery Opens
With The Ringing Of The Bell]

318
00:17:34,387 --> 00:17:37,857
[We Are Open]

319
00:17:41,093 --> 00:17:45,298
[Bonjour Bakery]
[Day 4, Open For Business]

320
00:17:45,298 --> 00:17:47,299
Here they come.

321
00:17:49,769 --> 00:17:51,671
[The First Customers Arrive On Day 4]
Come on in.

322
00:17:51,671 --> 00:17:53,339
Hello.

323
00:17:53,339 --> 00:17:55,875
[Loading Greeting Protocol]
When a customer comes in, say "Welcome!"

324
00:17:55,875 --> 00:17:58,110
[Processing Greeting]
Welcome. Hello.

325
00:17:58,110 --> 00:17:59,679
- Hello.
- Come this way.

326
00:17:59,679 --> 00:18:00,946
[Second Group Of Customers Arrives]

327
00:18:01,714 --> 00:18:03,782
[Loading Assisting Protocol]
Take the menu over.

328
00:18:04,450 --> 00:18:07,186
[Processing Assisting]
Bring out warm towels and menus.

329
00:18:07,954 --> 00:18:09,121
All right.

330
00:18:12,091 --> 00:18:14,827
[Error Processing Warm Towels And Menus]

331
00:18:15,595 --> 00:18:17,730
It's okay.

332
00:18:19,966 --> 00:18:21,300
Pace yourself, Seong Wu.

333
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:24,236
There's no need to hurry.

334
00:18:24,236 --> 00:18:26,572
[Rebooting]

335
00:18:27,473 --> 00:18:28,474
Here's the menu.

336
00:18:28,474 --> 00:18:31,377
[Menu Delivered Successfully]
I'll come back to get your order.

337
00:18:31,377 --> 00:18:33,312
- It's so nice and warm.
- It's warm.

338
00:18:33,312 --> 00:18:34,380
[Kim Hye Jin, Kim Hak Seon,
Hong Seung Yeon, Oh I Sun]

339
00:18:34,380 --> 00:18:37,917
All your favorite flowers are in here.

340
00:18:37,917 --> 00:18:41,287
There are some in that corner.

341
00:18:44,090 --> 00:18:46,759
They've got all the flowers you like.

342
00:18:46,759 --> 00:18:47,827
Isn't it pretty here?

343
00:18:47,827 --> 00:18:51,864
[Taking In All The Flowers]

344
00:18:51,864 --> 00:18:53,899
They're even on the menu, Mom.

345
00:18:53,899 --> 00:18:55,601
Your favorite thing is on the menu.

346
00:18:55,601 --> 00:18:57,436
They're flowers.

347
00:18:57,436 --> 00:18:59,105
- Oh, this?
- That's a tart?

348
00:18:59,105 --> 00:19:00,072
[Flowers Even On The Menu]

349
00:19:00,072 --> 00:19:01,140
They're today's new item.

350
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:02,842
- I see.
- It's so tasty and pretty.

351
00:19:02,842 --> 00:19:04,577
It's almost a shame to eat it.

352
00:19:04,577 --> 00:19:05,711
It is!

353
00:19:05,711 --> 00:19:08,080
You should try that one, Mom.

354
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:09,548
I'll get the dessert ready,

355
00:19:09,548 --> 00:19:11,350
- and you can make the Americano.
- Okay.

356
00:19:12,218 --> 00:19:15,554
[Iced Americano Output Successful]

357
00:19:15,554 --> 00:19:18,591
[Provide Prompt Service To Minimize Waiting]

358
00:19:18,591 --> 00:19:20,192
- Place them here.
- I hope you enjoy it.

359
00:19:20,192 --> 00:19:21,660
- Take a photo.
- Okay.

360
00:19:22,561 --> 00:19:23,829
Can I cut it?

361
00:19:23,829 --> 00:19:25,197
It might make a mess.

362
00:19:25,197 --> 00:19:27,199
Cut carefully.

363
00:19:27,199 --> 00:19:29,735
- We have everything, right?
- You can eat the flowers, right?

364
00:19:29,735 --> 00:19:30,803
Of course.

365
00:19:30,803 --> 00:19:33,673
Why else would they put it on the dessert?

366
00:19:33,673 --> 00:19:35,675
It's made of locally grown ingredients.

367
00:19:35,675 --> 00:19:36,976
[Let's Try A Taste Of This Pretty Flower]

368
00:19:36,976 --> 00:19:39,278
It should be good.

369
00:19:39,278 --> 00:19:42,615
[How Was The Dessert?]

370
00:19:42,615 --> 00:19:44,283
I'm so happy.

371
00:19:44,283 --> 00:19:46,185
I'm on cloud nine.

372
00:19:46,185 --> 00:19:49,088
It was so nice and scenic.

373
00:19:49,088 --> 00:19:50,823
- The desserts were so tasty, too.
- Okay.

374
00:19:50,823 --> 00:19:52,558
I enjoyed all of it.

375
00:19:52,558 --> 00:19:53,959
It was all great.

376
00:19:53,959 --> 00:19:56,996
Every part of that experience

377
00:19:56,996 --> 00:19:58,831
is etched into my memory.

378
00:19:58,831 --> 00:20:02,501
Thank you for such a joyful experience.

379
00:20:02,501 --> 00:20:06,338
It was lovely. I love you all.

380
00:20:09,175 --> 00:20:10,176
[Wailing]

381
00:20:10,176 --> 00:20:11,510
She's crying.

382
00:20:11,510 --> 00:20:14,079
- Do you want to add some sugar?
- No sugar.

383
00:20:15,247 --> 00:20:17,616
[Wailing]

384
00:20:17,616 --> 00:20:20,619
[An Unhappy Baby Customer]

385
00:20:20,619 --> 00:20:22,021
What's with the tears?

386
00:20:22,021 --> 00:20:23,422
- Oh, dear.
- Say hello.

387
00:20:23,422 --> 00:20:24,457
Is she shy?

388
00:20:24,457 --> 00:20:25,991
Not really.

389
00:20:26,525 --> 00:20:29,862
Stay here with me while they have dessert.

390
00:20:30,730 --> 00:20:32,631
She's stopped crying.

391
00:20:32,631 --> 00:20:33,532
[No More Tears]

392
00:20:33,532 --> 00:20:36,168
Thanks for not crying.

393
00:20:37,236 --> 00:20:38,671
[Giving The Customers A Chance
To Enjoy Themselves]

394
00:20:38,671 --> 00:20:40,305
Are you looking at Daddy?

395
00:20:41,741 --> 00:20:43,509
You're so cute.

396
00:20:43,509 --> 00:20:44,577
[We Also Offer Babysitting Service]

397
00:20:44,577 --> 00:20:46,879
She's being unusually quiet.

398
00:20:46,879 --> 00:20:50,549
[Snuggled In Hee Ae's Embrace]

399
00:20:50,549 --> 00:20:53,919
Thanks to her, we can eat in peace.

400
00:20:53,919 --> 00:20:56,355
Try a bite of this, Mom.

401
00:20:56,355 --> 00:20:57,857
Here you go.

402
00:20:57,857 --> 00:20:59,158
[Takes A Bite]

403
00:20:59,158 --> 00:21:00,159
Isn't it good?

404
00:21:00,159 --> 00:21:02,495
Apparently, it's lychee.

405
00:21:02,495 --> 00:21:04,997
The pastry is so good.

406
00:21:04,997 --> 00:21:07,833
[Eating In Peace
For The First Time In A While]

407
00:21:07,833 --> 00:21:09,902
- Goodbye.
- Thank you. Bye!

408
00:21:09,902 --> 00:21:11,804
[Leaving With Happy Smiles]
Thank you.

409
00:21:11,804 --> 00:21:13,606
Have a nice day.

410
00:21:13,606 --> 00:21:16,876
[A Quiet Moment
After The First Wave Of Customers Leaves]

411
00:21:16,876 --> 00:21:18,611
Since it's the weekend,

412
00:21:18,611 --> 00:21:21,080
I thought people would be lining up.

413
00:21:21,080 --> 00:21:22,414
I know, right?

414
00:21:22,414 --> 00:21:24,216
It's not going as I expected.

415
00:21:25,384 --> 00:21:30,589
[The Village Is Especially Quiet Today]

416
00:21:31,157 --> 00:21:34,960
[It Turns Out The Senior Residents
Leave Town For Errands On The Weekends]

417
00:21:37,663 --> 00:21:38,964
What on earth?

418
00:21:38,964 --> 00:21:40,199
- It's empty?
- They all left?

419
00:21:40,199 --> 00:21:41,567
- It's Saturday, though.
- They all left.

420
00:21:41,567 --> 00:21:43,269
- Really?
- Yes.

421
00:21:43,269 --> 00:21:45,070
We have so many pretty items
on the menu today.

422
00:21:45,070 --> 00:21:46,972
Tell me about it.

423
00:21:46,972 --> 00:21:51,210
[This Won't Do]

424
00:21:51,844 --> 00:21:55,247
[Chef Cha Steps Outside
For The First Time To Attract Customers]

425
00:21:55,247 --> 00:21:58,818
Where has everyone gone?

426
00:21:58,818 --> 00:21:59,819
Hello?

427
00:21:59,819 --> 00:22:04,323
[His Greeting Is Met By Silence]
<i>Hello?</i>

428
00:22:04,323 --> 00:22:07,026
- The streets are completely empty.
- Yeah.

429
00:22:07,026 --> 00:22:08,761
Even the streets are...

430
00:22:08,761 --> 00:22:11,197
[Spots Something]

431
00:22:11,197 --> 00:22:12,631
Isn't this a green barley field?

432
00:22:12,631 --> 00:22:14,666
- That's right.
- This field here.

433
00:22:16,035 --> 00:22:18,404
It's so nice. Look at the sky.

434
00:22:18,404 --> 00:22:20,005
It's unbelievable.

435
00:22:20,539 --> 00:22:24,610
[His Eyes Are Drawn
To The Beautifully Clear Sky]

436
00:22:25,177 --> 00:22:29,248
[He Couldn't Enjoy This View
While Working In The Kitchen]

437
00:22:29,815 --> 00:22:31,750
[A Stunning Spring Landscape]

438
00:22:31,750 --> 00:22:33,719
It's so nice.

439
00:22:35,287 --> 00:22:38,090
The weather is gorgeous.

440
00:22:38,090 --> 00:22:40,926
Now, it really feels like spring.

441
00:22:40,926 --> 00:22:42,561
- Don't you think?
- Yeah.

442
00:22:44,129 --> 00:22:45,965
Hang on. If this continues...

443
00:22:45,965 --> 00:22:48,400
Is someone coming?

444
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:49,301
Never mind.

445
00:22:49,301 --> 00:22:51,170
- Are they?
- It seems like...

446
00:22:51,170 --> 00:22:53,172
[Come On In]
They're coming in.

447
00:22:53,172 --> 00:22:54,640
Hello.

448
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:56,542
- I want something for my daughter-in-law.
- All right.

449
00:22:56,542 --> 00:22:59,345
- Pick some bread for me.
- Any type of bread?

450
00:22:59,345 --> 00:23:01,881
- Three of these...
- It's 3,000 won for one.

451
00:23:01,881 --> 00:23:02,781
I'll take it.

452
00:23:02,781 --> 00:23:03,682
[Another Person Has Tagged Along]

453
00:23:03,682 --> 00:23:05,918
- Do you want the set of three?
- Give me whatever.

454
00:23:05,918 --> 00:23:07,486
You're here again?

455
00:23:10,589 --> 00:23:13,926
[Standing In Silence]
Do you want it gift-wrapped or just...

456
00:23:13,926 --> 00:23:17,229
- I'll just take it.
- You'll take it as it is? Okay.

457
00:23:17,963 --> 00:23:20,032
I just came by for no reason.

458
00:23:20,032 --> 00:23:21,333
You came for no reason?

459
00:23:24,169 --> 00:23:26,906
[I Just Followed My Friend In Here]

460
00:23:26,906 --> 00:23:31,443
[But Seeing You Wrap Up That Bread...]

461
00:23:31,443 --> 00:23:33,545
Give me two of those.

462
00:23:33,545 --> 00:23:35,681
- Two citron madeleines?
- Yes.

463
00:23:35,681 --> 00:23:38,284
[I Want To Try A Taste]
How would you like to pay?

464
00:23:38,284 --> 00:23:39,618
Do you want to pay in cash or...

465
00:23:39,618 --> 00:23:41,387
I came empty-handed.

466
00:23:41,387 --> 00:23:42,288
[I Didn't Bring My Wallet]
Really?

467
00:23:42,288 --> 00:23:43,188
- It's 6,000 won?
- Yes.

468
00:23:43,188 --> 00:23:44,757
- I'll bring it later.
- Okay.

469
00:23:44,757 --> 00:23:46,158
Hand it over.

470
00:23:46,158 --> 00:23:47,159
I'll come back.

471
00:23:47,159 --> 00:23:48,060
- Sure.
- Okay.

472
00:23:48,060 --> 00:23:49,528
[An Unplanned Tab Transaction]

473
00:23:49,528 --> 00:23:51,830
I'm sorry.

474
00:23:51,830 --> 00:23:53,332
- Don't you have any red ones?
- Sorry?

475
00:23:53,332 --> 00:23:54,967
Are they all this color?

476
00:23:54,967 --> 00:23:56,201
- Do you mean the bag?
- Yes.

477
00:23:56,201 --> 00:23:57,903
- Yes, they're all this color.
- I see.

478
00:23:57,903 --> 00:23:59,037
Yes.

479
00:24:03,642 --> 00:24:05,911
Goodbye. Thank you.

480
00:24:05,911 --> 00:24:07,980
Thank you.

481
00:24:07,980 --> 00:24:09,248
[On Day 4 Of Business]
About 6,000 won...

482
00:24:09,248 --> 00:24:11,817
- It's on her tab.
- Right.

483
00:24:11,817 --> 00:24:13,285
[There's Already A Nameless Tab]
As for her name...

484
00:24:13,285 --> 00:24:16,188
Write down "Purple-haired Lady's Friend."

485
00:24:16,188 --> 00:24:18,223
- "Purple-hair..."
- Purple...

486
00:24:18,223 --> 00:24:20,726
[Repeating For Confirmation]
"Purple-haired Lady's Friend."

487
00:24:20,726 --> 00:24:23,595
[Writing It Down Word-For-Word]

488
00:24:25,297 --> 00:24:26,966
[Purple-Haired Lady's Friend]
[2 Citron Madeleines On The Tab]

489
00:24:26,966 --> 00:24:28,467
"Purple-haired Lady's Friend."

490
00:24:28,467 --> 00:24:30,703
That's small-town business for you.

491
00:24:30,703 --> 00:24:33,071
[A Moment Later]

492
00:24:34,073 --> 00:24:35,407
Hello.

493
00:24:35,407 --> 00:24:36,976
Hello, you're back.

494
00:24:36,976 --> 00:24:39,345
- I came to pay.
- You brought the money?

495
00:24:39,345 --> 00:24:41,146
We'll sort that for you over there.

496
00:24:41,146 --> 00:24:43,882
I appreciate your hard work.

497
00:24:43,882 --> 00:24:45,117
- Thank you.
- Not at all.

498
00:24:45,117 --> 00:24:47,353
It's nice to have you in our neighborhood.

499
00:24:47,353 --> 00:24:49,088
- Thank you.
- Goodbye.

500
00:24:49,088 --> 00:24:50,956
Goodbye.

501
00:24:52,124 --> 00:24:53,025
Have a nice day.

502
00:24:53,025 --> 00:24:54,159
- I'll enjoy these.
- Okay.

503
00:24:54,159 --> 00:24:55,527
- All right.
- Thank you. Take care.

504
00:24:55,527 --> 00:24:56,895
Goodbye.

505
00:24:59,098 --> 00:25:01,466
Clean up after a customer leaves.

506
00:25:07,873 --> 00:25:11,677
[Current Time: 1 P.M.]

507
00:25:11,677 --> 00:25:14,446
[Current Status:]

508
00:25:14,446 --> 00:25:18,751
[0 Customers]

509
00:25:18,751 --> 00:25:22,755
It's the complete opposite
of what we expected.

510
00:25:22,755 --> 00:25:24,490
- Right?
- Yeah.

511
00:25:24,490 --> 00:25:28,027
[First Day Part-Timer Dino]
When Chan was here,

512
00:25:28,027 --> 00:25:29,962
[Came To Help On A Hectic Day]
he was worked to the bone.

513
00:25:29,962 --> 00:25:31,296
He had to stay alert.

514
00:25:31,296 --> 00:25:32,898
He was exhausted by the end of the day.

515
00:25:32,898 --> 00:25:33,832
[There's A Story That Exhausted Chan]

516
00:25:33,832 --> 00:25:36,735
I heard he went home in his uniform.

517
00:25:36,735 --> 00:25:38,504
[Went Home Without Even Changing]

518
00:25:38,504 --> 00:25:41,273
[Hee Ae Loves This Anecdote]

519
00:25:42,374 --> 00:25:44,109
He did a great job, though.

520
00:25:45,711 --> 00:25:49,014
[An Unusually Quiet Day]

521
00:25:49,014 --> 00:25:52,818
[What Is A Manager To Do?]

522
00:25:54,787 --> 00:25:58,290
[The Manager's Quick Side Duties]
[A Quick Style-Check]

523
00:25:59,792 --> 00:26:02,528
I find the lattes really tricky.

524
00:26:02,528 --> 00:26:06,298
It's hard when we get orders
for a latte and a hot Americano

525
00:26:06,298 --> 00:26:08,367
[Listening To Part-Timer Concerns]
at the same time.

526
00:26:09,635 --> 00:26:12,971
[Our Part-Timer Seems Troubled]

527
00:26:12,971 --> 00:26:15,874
[I'd Better Make A Lemon Honey Tea]

528
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:21,814
[A Lemon-Honey Base With Real Fruit Pulp]

529
00:26:21,814 --> 00:26:26,618
[All You Need Is Half A Cup]

530
00:26:27,553 --> 00:26:29,955
[They Say It's Good To Stick Together]

531
00:26:29,955 --> 00:26:33,325
[But You Don't Want Clumps Of Ice]

532
00:26:36,328 --> 00:26:37,763
[Adjust The Concentration
For The Perfect Balance]

533
00:26:37,763 --> 00:26:40,732
[And Add Some Freshly-Squeezed Lemon Juice]

534
00:26:42,501 --> 00:26:47,472
[The Gift Of A Sweet And Sour Sip Of Joy]

535
00:26:49,341 --> 00:26:53,311
[A Gift For Myself]

536
00:26:54,046 --> 00:26:55,747
[Smiling Gently]
Do you want a cup?

537
00:26:55,747 --> 00:26:56,949
I'm okay.

538
00:26:56,949 --> 00:26:59,251
It's good even without sparkling water.

539
00:27:00,819 --> 00:27:03,689
[Just Then]

540
00:27:03,689 --> 00:27:07,726
[The Long Lull Is Broken By New Customers]

541
00:27:08,627 --> 00:27:10,462
- It's a famous bakery.
- Welcome.

542
00:27:10,462 --> 00:27:11,863
Hello.

543
00:27:12,798 --> 00:27:14,233
See?

544
00:27:14,233 --> 00:27:15,701
They're here to see celebrities.

545
00:27:15,701 --> 00:27:17,069
- Oh, right.
- I see.

546
00:27:17,069 --> 00:27:18,804
- Who's the celebrity?
- Sorry?

547
00:27:18,804 --> 00:27:20,439
[Looking For Celebrities]
Who's the celebrity?

548
00:27:20,439 --> 00:27:22,808
[In Front Of Celebrities]
Is it them?

549
00:27:23,408 --> 00:27:25,844
[This Excited Customer Looks Familiar]

550
00:27:26,678 --> 00:27:28,814
[One Week Ago]

551
00:27:28,814 --> 00:27:30,649
Do you live alone?

552
00:27:30,649 --> 00:27:32,651
You mean, where is my wife?

553
00:27:32,651 --> 00:27:33,652
Yes.

554
00:27:33,652 --> 00:27:34,887
My wife is in heaven.

555
00:27:34,887 --> 00:27:36,822
I'm sorry.

556
00:27:37,389 --> 00:27:39,691
[He Came To The Bakery Alone]

557
00:27:40,692 --> 00:27:44,696
[But He's Back With His Family
For His 90th Birthday]

558
00:27:44,696 --> 00:27:47,265
[He Came Hand-In-Hand
With His Great-Grandson]

559
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:49,968
- I'm sitting here.
- Take a seat.

560
00:27:49,968 --> 00:27:52,070
[Im Chae Dong]
This is my seat.

561
00:27:52,070 --> 00:27:55,240
- We came to see the staff.
- There's another chair here.

562
00:27:55,240 --> 00:27:57,409
[She Never Forgets A Face]
But you've been here before.

563
00:27:57,409 --> 00:27:58,877
- What?
- Isn't this your second visit?

564
00:27:58,877 --> 00:28:00,279
I'm talking about my daughter.

565
00:28:00,279 --> 00:28:01,847
[The Kids Wanted To See Celebrities]
Oh, I see.

566
00:28:01,847 --> 00:28:03,348
Your family was curious.

567
00:28:04,149 --> 00:28:05,884
[He Still Doesn't Know Who's Who]
Your family wanted to come?

568
00:28:05,884 --> 00:28:07,686
- Okay.
- Okay.

569
00:28:07,686 --> 00:28:09,488
Order for yourselves. I'm not hungry.

570
00:28:09,488 --> 00:28:12,157
- Are you treating us, Dad?
- What?

571
00:28:12,157 --> 00:28:14,726
- You're paying, right?
- Sure.

572
00:28:14,726 --> 00:28:17,229
[Effortlessly Cool At 90]
It's on me.

573
00:28:17,229 --> 00:28:19,298
[Laughter]

574
00:28:19,298 --> 00:28:22,234
He's in a great mood today.

575
00:28:22,234 --> 00:28:24,102
[He's Puffed Up With Pride]

576
00:28:24,102 --> 00:28:26,705
[Come To Think Of It]

577
00:28:26,705 --> 00:28:31,543
[He Was Much Quieter
When He Came On His Own]

578
00:28:31,543 --> 00:28:32,945
I bet he'll enjoy it more today.

579
00:28:32,945 --> 00:28:33,979
[But Today]
Yeah.

580
00:28:33,979 --> 00:28:36,915
What is that? Is it bread or what?

581
00:28:36,915 --> 00:28:39,518
[He Can't Contain His Curiosity]
What is that? Is it bread or what?

582
00:28:39,518 --> 00:28:41,086
- Is it an oak carving?
- No.

583
00:28:41,086 --> 00:28:42,588
- It's called a baguette.
- What?

584
00:28:42,588 --> 00:28:43,822
It's a baguette.

585
00:28:43,822 --> 00:28:46,225
- This...
- Do you drive, Ji Yeong?

586
00:28:46,225 --> 00:28:48,026
You need to be careful.

587
00:28:48,894 --> 00:28:50,996
She's a great driver now.

588
00:28:50,996 --> 00:28:53,565
Knowing that you're old enough to drive

589
00:28:53,565 --> 00:28:57,702
gives me this tingling feeling.

590
00:29:00,372 --> 00:29:01,873
[On This Special Day]

591
00:29:01,873 --> 00:29:04,776
- This looks like a question mark.
- Where?

592
00:29:04,776 --> 00:29:07,279
[His Heart Flutters In A Strangely New Way]

593
00:29:13,318 --> 00:29:18,890
[He Just Needs A Slice Of A Dessert
That Captures His Feelings]

594
00:29:19,591 --> 00:29:23,262
Here are your drinks and desserts.

595
00:29:23,262 --> 00:29:25,130
Did someone just bake these?

596
00:29:25,130 --> 00:29:26,898
- Do you know Cha Seung Won?
- Yes.

597
00:29:26,898 --> 00:29:29,001
He made these.

598
00:29:29,001 --> 00:29:31,403
This lady appears on TV, Dad.

599
00:29:31,403 --> 00:29:33,639
Dad didn't know when he came last week.

600
00:29:33,639 --> 00:29:34,940
You appear on TV?

601
00:29:34,940 --> 00:29:37,175
Don't you recognize her?

602
00:29:37,175 --> 00:29:40,746
- What do you appear in?
- Thank you.

603
00:29:40,746 --> 00:29:42,681
Show him some clips.

604
00:29:42,681 --> 00:29:43,915
Show him quickly.

605
00:29:43,915 --> 00:29:46,918
[He Learned The Truth
About The Manager After A Week]

606
00:29:46,918 --> 00:29:48,754
That's enough. I'm too full to eat it all.

607
00:29:48,754 --> 00:29:49,821
Try a bite.

608
00:29:49,821 --> 00:29:51,189
I'm not hungry.

609
00:29:51,189 --> 00:29:52,858
- Try some.
- Just one bite.

610
00:29:52,858 --> 00:29:54,593
[Dessert Seems Far From His Mind]
Seriously.

611
00:29:54,593 --> 00:29:59,131
[Is Something Bothering Him?]

612
00:29:59,131 --> 00:30:02,000
[He Wanders Out]

613
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:04,235
[He Pokes The Baguette]

614
00:30:05,704 --> 00:30:07,506
But...

615
00:30:07,506 --> 00:30:10,108
You won't earn much in the countryside.

616
00:30:10,108 --> 00:30:12,878
What made you set up shop here?

617
00:30:12,878 --> 00:30:14,046
[He's Concerned About The Lack Of Customers]

618
00:30:14,046 --> 00:30:16,715
- You're worried on our behalf.
- I see.

619
00:30:16,715 --> 00:30:18,016
Since this is a rural area...

620
00:30:18,016 --> 00:30:20,919
[Young Celebrities
Don't Understand The Real World]

621
00:30:20,919 --> 00:30:23,922
But it's so lovely here.

622
00:30:23,922 --> 00:30:25,157
That may be so,

623
00:30:25,157 --> 00:30:26,558
but you won't make much money.

624
00:30:26,558 --> 00:30:28,694
- Do you have a healthy appetite?
- Yes.

625
00:30:28,694 --> 00:30:29,995
To eat is to live.

626
00:30:29,995 --> 00:30:31,330
That's true.

627
00:30:31,330 --> 00:30:33,832
- Didn't you come alone last time?
- Yes.

628
00:30:33,832 --> 00:30:35,500
I remember.

629
00:30:35,500 --> 00:30:37,402
You have a good memory.

630
00:30:38,770 --> 00:30:41,073
Will you leave again next week?

631
00:30:41,073 --> 00:30:42,841
We'll be here until Tuesday.

632
00:30:42,841 --> 00:30:44,710
- You're leaving on Tuesday?
- Yes.

633
00:30:44,710 --> 00:30:45,977
When will you be back?

634
00:30:45,977 --> 00:30:47,312
After next week,

635
00:30:47,312 --> 00:30:48,847
if we do well, we'll be back.

636
00:30:48,847 --> 00:30:51,082
If not, that will be the end of it.

637
00:30:52,584 --> 00:30:54,853
Then you'll pack up for good?

638
00:30:54,853 --> 00:30:56,688
Yes.

639
00:30:59,091 --> 00:31:01,226
[I Hope Business Goes Well]
Can I get a glass of water?

640
00:31:01,226 --> 00:31:03,495
Do you want it hot or cold?

641
00:31:03,495 --> 00:31:06,464
- I want it warm.
- Warm water? Okay.

642
00:31:08,166 --> 00:31:12,104
I wondered who Kim Hee Ae was.

643
00:31:12,104 --> 00:31:13,805
Here's your water.

644
00:31:21,179 --> 00:31:22,948
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

645
00:31:22,948 --> 00:31:24,149
Take care.

646
00:31:24,149 --> 00:31:25,751
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

647
00:31:25,751 --> 00:31:27,719
Thank you.

648
00:31:29,788 --> 00:31:32,090
[At That Moment]

649
00:31:32,090 --> 00:31:33,992
I want to do my best.

650
00:31:33,992 --> 00:31:37,395
I really want to pull this off.

651
00:31:39,064 --> 00:31:40,165
<i>Bokbunja</i> Croissant...

652
00:31:40,165 --> 00:31:42,200
[Chef Cha Mutters &lt;I&gt;Bokbunja&lt;/I&gt; Croissant]
<i>Bokbunja</i> Croissant.

653
00:31:42,901 --> 00:31:45,670
[Bonjour <i>Bokbunja</i> Croissant]

654
00:31:45,670 --> 00:31:48,273
[A Crescent Moon In Name And Shape]

655
00:31:49,408 --> 00:31:51,076
[Butter Is Folded Into The Dough]

656
00:31:51,076 --> 00:31:54,579
[To Make A Multi-Layered Pastry]

657
00:31:54,579 --> 00:31:56,448
[Multiple Layers]

658
00:31:56,982 --> 00:31:59,217
[Crispy On The Outside]

659
00:31:59,217 --> 00:32:02,887
[And Filled With A Sweet Jam
Made Of Gochang's <i>Bokbunja</i>]

660
00:32:05,991 --> 00:32:07,058
Bonjour!

661
00:32:07,058 --> 00:32:08,059
<i>Bokbunja!</i>

662
00:32:08,059 --> 00:32:09,361
Croissant!

663
00:32:09,361 --> 00:32:11,496
[Bonjour <i>Bokbunja</i> Croissant]

664
00:32:12,931 --> 00:32:16,001
[Munching Away In Her Sleep]

665
00:32:16,001 --> 00:32:17,469
[Let's Make The Dough]

666
00:32:17,469 --> 00:32:19,638
Have it mixed for eight minutes...

667
00:32:19,638 --> 00:32:21,706
[Combine Sugar, Salt
Yeast, Flour, And Butter]

668
00:32:21,706 --> 00:32:23,775
[To Make The Croissant Dough]

669
00:32:23,775 --> 00:32:27,212
[Split The Completed Dough In Half]

670
00:32:27,212 --> 00:32:30,749
[Rest At Room Temperature For 20 Minutes]

671
00:32:33,518 --> 00:32:35,587
[Take The Remaining Dough]

672
00:32:35,587 --> 00:32:38,990
[And Add Butter And <i>Bokbunja</i> Powder]

673
00:32:41,092 --> 00:32:43,528
It's a Pyongyang dumpling.

674
00:32:43,528 --> 00:32:46,431
Pyongyang dumpling.

675
00:32:47,132 --> 00:32:51,269
[The Pyongyang Dumpling
Will Form The Red Pastry]

676
00:32:51,269 --> 00:32:54,606
[Put The Pyongyang Dumpling
Back In The Mixer]

677
00:32:57,375 --> 00:33:01,446
[Watch It Transform
Into A Red <i>Bokbunja</i> Dough]

678
00:33:03,348 --> 00:33:09,855
[Roll It Out To Size]

679
00:33:09,855 --> 00:33:11,223
[While The <i>Bokbunja</i> Dough Rests]

680
00:33:11,223 --> 00:33:14,025
[It's Time To Make The <i>Bokbunja</i> Jam!]

681
00:33:14,025 --> 00:33:16,595
[<i>Bokbunja</i> Puree]

682
00:33:16,595 --> 00:33:19,598
[Cornstarch And Sugar]

683
00:33:19,598 --> 00:33:22,868
[Mix The <i>Bokbunja</i> Puree
With The Cornstarch And Sugar]

684
00:33:22,868 --> 00:33:25,336
[And Boil It For 1 Minute]

685
00:33:29,207 --> 00:33:31,242
That's looking good.

686
00:33:32,310 --> 00:33:33,845
[Ki Taek Makes The Jam
With His Strong Forearm]

687
00:33:33,845 --> 00:33:35,446
- It's good.
- Okay.

688
00:33:36,948 --> 00:33:40,552
[Portion 15G Into Each Mold]

689
00:33:40,552 --> 00:33:45,523
[The <i>Bokbunja</i> Jam
Goes Straight Into The Fridge]

690
00:33:47,292 --> 00:33:48,827
[Once The 1st Proof Is Complete]

691
00:33:48,827 --> 00:33:52,063
[It's Time To Add Butter
To The Croissant Dough]

692
00:33:56,368 --> 00:33:59,771
[The Butter Between The Layers Of Dough]

693
00:33:59,771 --> 00:34:03,408
[Create The Croissant's Signature Texture]

694
00:34:03,942 --> 00:34:08,346
[It's Key To Maintain An Even Thickness]

695
00:34:09,247 --> 00:34:14,018
[Pie Roller]
[A Machine That Keeps Thickness Consistent]

696
00:34:17,722 --> 00:34:19,290
[Perfect Dough Length]
Okay, that's 80.

697
00:34:23,662 --> 00:34:25,597
[Once The Thickness Is Just Right]

698
00:34:25,597 --> 00:34:29,267
[The Red <i>Bokbunja</i> Dough Is Placed On Top]

699
00:34:33,338 --> 00:34:39,644
[Once The Combined Dough
Has Been Rolled To Size]

700
00:34:41,613 --> 00:34:43,781
Place it on the table.

701
00:34:44,783 --> 00:34:47,385
[It's Time To Trim The Dough]

702
00:34:52,958 --> 00:34:56,895
[Cut It To A Length Of 30cm
And Square Off The Corners]

703
00:35:13,111 --> 00:35:16,481
[Cut A Small Notch For Easier Rolling]

704
00:35:19,384 --> 00:35:20,452
[<i>Bokbunja</i> Jam]

705
00:35:20,452 --> 00:35:25,056
[Add The Jam And Roll The Dough
To Shape The Croissant]

706
00:35:35,767 --> 00:35:41,272
[Proof For 2 Hours After Shaping]

707
00:35:52,183 --> 00:35:58,489
[Egg Wash Coating
For A Shiny Glaze And Extra Crispiness]

708
00:36:08,333 --> 00:36:14,172
[Bake In The Oven For 15 Minutes]

709
00:36:14,172 --> 00:36:15,807
Look at that.

710
00:36:21,346 --> 00:36:26,551
They came out so nicely.

711
00:36:26,551 --> 00:36:30,121
I think they'll love them.

712
00:36:30,889 --> 00:36:33,825
[2:50 P.M.]

713
00:36:36,928 --> 00:36:39,397
[A New Item Is Added For The Afternoon Menu]

714
00:36:40,699 --> 00:36:41,866
[Today's New Morning Menu]

715
00:36:41,866 --> 00:36:44,769
[Captured The Bright Vibe Of Spring]

716
00:36:45,303 --> 00:36:48,373
[Today's New Afternoon Menu]

717
00:36:48,373 --> 00:36:50,241
[Is Deep And Rich Black]

718
00:36:52,510 --> 00:36:55,180
[A Deeply Rich, Nutty Flavor]

719
00:36:55,180 --> 00:36:58,116
[Bonjour Black Sesame Flan]

720
00:36:59,250 --> 00:37:00,752
- Is that the new item?
- Yes.

721
00:37:00,752 --> 00:37:03,354
It's the black sesame dessert.

722
00:37:03,354 --> 00:37:06,725
It's really nutty and so delicious.

723
00:37:06,725 --> 00:37:10,061
The black sesame feels premium.

724
00:37:10,061 --> 00:37:13,197
That's how it tastes to me.

725
00:37:13,932 --> 00:37:16,734
[As Ki Taek's Top New Pick Hits The Display]

726
00:37:22,273 --> 00:37:25,476
[The Bakery Opens For The Afternoon]

727
00:37:26,244 --> 00:37:30,214
[It's Afternoon In The Village
That Was Ghostly Quiet This Morning]

728
00:37:30,782 --> 00:37:34,219
[The Residents Have Returned Home]

729
00:37:34,219 --> 00:37:37,288
[And Visitors Have Come Into Town
For A Weekend Excursion]

730
00:37:39,023 --> 00:37:41,993
[So The Village Is Getting Livelier]

731
00:37:43,928 --> 00:37:46,631
I spy a group of senior men.

732
00:37:46,631 --> 00:37:51,870
It's rare to see senior men get together.

733
00:37:51,870 --> 00:37:54,239
- Hello.
- Hello.

734
00:37:54,239 --> 00:37:56,207
- It's nice to meet you.
- It's nice to meet you.

735
00:37:56,207 --> 00:37:58,543
- Hello.
- Welcome.

736
00:37:58,543 --> 00:38:00,278
- It's nice to meet you.
- Ask to see their IDs.

737
00:38:00,278 --> 00:38:03,281
- You must be over 65 years old.
- You just have to check one.

738
00:38:03,281 --> 00:38:04,415
Can I check your ID?

739
00:38:04,415 --> 00:38:08,953
- We're all old and over 70.
- I just need to see one.

740
00:38:08,953 --> 00:38:11,723
It's flattering to get your ID checked.

741
00:38:11,723 --> 00:38:14,058
It means you look young.

742
00:38:14,058 --> 00:38:16,194
You seem very familiar.

743
00:38:16,194 --> 00:38:18,263
- I'm sure I do.
- I've seen you before.

744
00:38:18,263 --> 00:38:19,864
She's my favorite celebrity.

745
00:38:19,864 --> 00:38:20,999
Thank you, sir.

746
00:38:20,999 --> 00:38:22,867
I mean it. You're my favorite star.

747
00:38:22,867 --> 00:38:25,570
My goodness. Thank you.

748
00:38:25,570 --> 00:38:26,971
Was it <i>My Wife's Husband</i>?

749
00:38:26,971 --> 00:38:29,140
Or <i>My Husband's Wife</i>?

750
00:38:29,140 --> 00:38:31,843
- Yeah, <i>My Husband's Woman</i>.
- I watched it countless times.

751
00:38:31,843 --> 00:38:32,744
Goodness.

752
00:38:32,744 --> 00:38:33,978
[She Won Her 5th Grand Prize]
Thank you.

753
00:38:33,978 --> 00:38:35,079
[For The Hit Romance Drama]

754
00:38:35,079 --> 00:38:38,850
- You're my favorite Korean actress.
- Right.

755
00:38:38,850 --> 00:38:41,352
[Fourth Time Saying It]
I mean it. You're my absolute favorite.

756
00:38:41,352 --> 00:38:43,087
Thank you.

757
00:38:43,087 --> 00:38:46,658
[Kim Yeong Tae, Im Dong Gwan,
Sung Gyeong Gi, Lee Gi Bong]

758
00:38:46,658 --> 00:38:47,892
Excuse me.

759
00:38:47,892 --> 00:38:49,127
- Are you ready to order?
- Yes.

760
00:38:49,127 --> 00:38:50,662
- What's this?
- Let's see.

761
00:38:50,662 --> 00:38:53,531
It's the <i>Bokbunja</i> Croissant
filled with <i>bokbunja</i> jam.

762
00:38:53,531 --> 00:38:55,266
<i>- Bokbunja...</i>
- We have it all the time.

763
00:38:55,266 --> 00:38:58,269
We have it every day.

764
00:38:58,269 --> 00:39:01,005
- Do you have it every day?
- This is our hometown.

765
00:39:01,005 --> 00:39:03,708
We grew up here,
and <i>bokbunja</i> is the local specialty.

766
00:39:03,708 --> 00:39:05,276
Give us four of these.

767
00:39:05,276 --> 00:39:06,878
Any of these will do.

768
00:39:06,878 --> 00:39:08,379
- A selection of these small ones?
- Yes.

769
00:39:08,379 --> 00:39:10,114
- Four madeleines?
- Yeah.

770
00:39:10,114 --> 00:39:12,383
Just give us a random selection.

771
00:39:12,383 --> 00:39:13,852
[Since Gochang Is The Land Of <i>Bokbunja</i>]

772
00:39:13,852 --> 00:39:17,488
[For The Four Friends
Who Are Local To The Area]

773
00:39:17,488 --> 00:39:21,159
[We Put Together
A Set Of 4 Different Baked Goods]

774
00:39:24,062 --> 00:39:27,899
- I've followed you since your debut,
- I see.

775
00:39:27,899 --> 00:39:31,402
since you starred in that drama
with Baek Il Sub.

776
00:39:31,402 --> 00:39:33,204
<i>- Son and Daughter?</i>
- That's right.

777
00:39:33,204 --> 00:39:35,807
- I've seen all your works.
- My goodness.

778
00:39:35,807 --> 00:39:37,942
- I'm so touched.
- I'm a real fan.

779
00:39:38,643 --> 00:39:40,812
- Enjoy. Thank you.
- All right.

780
00:39:40,812 --> 00:39:42,814
[Served By His Top Favorite Actress]

781
00:39:42,814 --> 00:39:46,250
[His First Ever French Dessert]

782
00:39:48,720 --> 00:39:51,222
Try it. It's tasty.

783
00:39:51,222 --> 00:39:53,758
We'd better order some more.

784
00:39:53,758 --> 00:39:55,860
[What About Dinner?]

785
00:40:00,164 --> 00:40:01,900
How do you know each other?

786
00:40:01,900 --> 00:40:04,302
- We're elementary school friends.
- We were schoolmates.

787
00:40:04,302 --> 00:40:06,104
We went to the same school.

788
00:40:06,104 --> 00:40:07,572
- Gapyeong Elementary School.
- That's right.

789
00:40:07,572 --> 00:40:10,642
We've been friends since birth.
We grew up together.

790
00:40:10,642 --> 00:40:12,911
[60 Years Of Friendship
Since Elementary School]

791
00:40:12,911 --> 00:40:15,413
None of us can handle a drink.

792
00:40:15,413 --> 00:40:17,348
We used to be heavy drinkers,

793
00:40:17,348 --> 00:40:18,816
but now that we're older...

794
00:40:18,816 --> 00:40:20,184
We're all in bad shape.

795
00:40:20,184 --> 00:40:21,819
We need to think about our health now.

796
00:40:21,819 --> 00:40:24,355
It's nice to get together

797
00:40:24,355 --> 00:40:27,225
for some tea and dessert.

798
00:40:27,225 --> 00:40:29,494
[Now That They're Retired Drinkers]

799
00:40:29,494 --> 00:40:35,466
[They Enjoy A Cozy Chat Over A Cup Of Tea]

800
00:40:37,235 --> 00:40:40,271
[How Was The Dessert?]

801
00:40:40,271 --> 00:40:42,340
Compared to the old days,

802
00:40:42,340 --> 00:40:46,311
it feels like a luxurious treat.

803
00:40:46,311 --> 00:40:48,112
We never had things like this growing up.

804
00:40:48,112 --> 00:40:50,915
Now that we get to try all these foods,

805
00:40:50,915 --> 00:40:53,351
everything tastes amazing.

806
00:40:53,351 --> 00:40:55,253
When we were younger,

807
00:40:55,253 --> 00:40:58,890
we got food from the American soldiers.

808
00:40:58,890 --> 00:41:00,992
They gave us cornbread.

809
00:41:00,992 --> 00:41:03,628
On winter nights,
we used to reach into the straw

810
00:41:03,628 --> 00:41:05,229
to catch sparrows.

811
00:41:05,229 --> 00:41:08,533
We used to roast and eat them
when we were younger.

812
00:41:08,533 --> 00:41:10,134
Since it was dark,

813
00:41:10,134 --> 00:41:11,836
sometimes we caught a snake instead.

814
00:41:11,836 --> 00:41:14,739
Yes, we sometimes caught a snake.

815
00:41:15,840 --> 00:41:19,610
[They Weathered The Lean Years Together]

816
00:41:20,144 --> 00:41:22,480
[And They're Still Friends To This Day]

817
00:41:22,480 --> 00:41:25,616
[Spending Warm And Sweet Moments Together]

818
00:41:27,885 --> 00:41:30,421
[Bonjour Bakery]

819
00:41:30,421 --> 00:41:32,490
[New Customers Wait At The Bakery]
They look so pretty planted like this.

820
00:41:32,490 --> 00:41:34,425
This one's bloomed already.

821
00:41:34,425 --> 00:41:36,294
There's bread right here.

822
00:41:36,294 --> 00:41:40,164
We don't need to bother going inside.
We can eat these.

823
00:41:40,164 --> 00:41:42,900
[A Group Of 4 Girlfriends Visit]
We can have these instead.

824
00:41:42,900 --> 00:41:45,970
[Following The 4 Schoolmates]
Try that stick of bread.

825
00:41:45,970 --> 00:41:47,905
[A Group Of Girlfriends]
Use these wet towels to wipe your hands.

826
00:41:47,905 --> 00:41:51,576
I'll come back to get your order
whenever you're ready.

827
00:41:51,576 --> 00:41:53,511
- Let's have one of these.
- Yes.

828
00:41:53,511 --> 00:41:55,646
- And one of these.
- Yes.

829
00:41:55,646 --> 00:41:56,547
And this one.

830
00:41:56,547 --> 00:41:58,049
Not that one.

831
00:41:58,049 --> 00:41:59,317
- I don't want <i>bokbunja</i>.
<i>- Bokbunja?</i>

832
00:41:59,317 --> 00:42:00,418
- This one.
- This one?

833
00:42:00,418 --> 00:42:04,322
We work at the <i>bokbunja</i> factory.

834
00:42:04,322 --> 00:42:06,591
- You don't want the <i>bokbunja</i>?
- No.

835
00:42:06,591 --> 00:42:08,793
[The Locals Are Surrounded By &lt;I&gt;Bokbunja&lt;/I&gt;]
The <i>bokbunja</i> is a no-go.

836
00:42:08,793 --> 00:42:11,829
- You look like someone on TV.
- Yes.

837
00:42:11,829 --> 00:42:13,965
- You're handsome.
- Do you recognize me?

838
00:42:13,965 --> 00:42:16,300
- Yes.
- I think I've seen you in a TV drama.

839
00:42:16,300 --> 00:42:18,136
You have a fine nose.

840
00:42:18,136 --> 00:42:20,705
[He's Very Handsome]

841
00:42:20,705 --> 00:42:22,140
[Playfully Cheeky]

842
00:42:22,140 --> 00:42:23,374
[Ong-Droid Return To Human Mode]
You saw me in a drama?

843
00:42:23,374 --> 00:42:24,642
That's right.

844
00:42:24,642 --> 00:42:26,744
- How are you so handsome?
- Thank you.

845
00:42:26,744 --> 00:42:29,047
You're very good-looking.

846
00:42:29,047 --> 00:42:32,016
- I'll bring the desserts in a flash.
- Okay.

847
00:42:32,016 --> 00:42:34,919
[The Handsome Part-Timer Is On It]
Wait just one moment.

848
00:42:44,695 --> 00:42:47,098
[Extracting Two Shots At Once]

849
00:42:47,932 --> 00:42:50,234
[Steamed Milk Is The Heart Of A Latte]

850
00:42:50,234 --> 00:42:53,904
[A Few Taps On The Counter
For A Silky-Smooth Foam]

851
00:42:54,639 --> 00:42:57,775
[He Draws A Shape With A Gentle Swirl]

852
00:42:58,709 --> 00:43:02,013
[It's A Heart]

853
00:43:02,013 --> 00:43:05,183
- Here are the two hot lattes first.
- All right.

854
00:43:05,183 --> 00:43:07,218
[Same Lattes, Different Shapes]

855
00:43:07,218 --> 00:43:08,986
- Ta-da.
- The pretty person

856
00:43:08,986 --> 00:43:10,955
should get the less pretty one.

857
00:43:13,524 --> 00:43:16,427
I'll try to do better next time.

858
00:43:16,427 --> 00:43:18,496
- Haven't you been here before?
- Yes.

859
00:43:18,496 --> 00:43:21,199
- I've been here before.
- You are such a pretty person.

860
00:43:21,199 --> 00:43:24,068
[She Visited On The 3rd Day]

861
00:43:25,536 --> 00:43:27,438
- Do you want to try this one?
- Yes.

862
00:43:27,438 --> 00:43:30,274
[She Came Back So Her Friends Could Try It]

863
00:43:32,944 --> 00:43:35,513
Drink the coffee before it gets cold.

864
00:43:35,513 --> 00:43:36,581
This bread is tasty.

865
00:43:36,581 --> 00:43:37,715
- Right?
- Yes.

866
00:43:37,715 --> 00:43:38,783
- This one?
- Yes.

867
00:43:38,783 --> 00:43:40,284
It's like a biscuit.

868
00:43:40,284 --> 00:43:41,986
This one.

869
00:43:43,187 --> 00:43:44,088
[She Brazenly Splits The Madeleine]

870
00:43:44,088 --> 00:43:45,890
You need to add sugar
if you like it sweet.

871
00:43:45,890 --> 00:43:47,959
Yes, you need sugar.

872
00:43:47,959 --> 00:43:49,427
- What about this one?
- No.

873
00:43:49,427 --> 00:43:51,162
- You don't need sugar?
- No.

874
00:43:51,162 --> 00:43:52,830
[Four Equal Portions]

875
00:43:52,830 --> 00:43:55,333
- You like it sweet.
- I do.

876
00:43:55,333 --> 00:43:59,236
She ripped apart the cake with her hands.

877
00:44:01,539 --> 00:44:05,276
[Casually Reaches For Another Madeleine]
She ripped them with her hands.

878
00:44:05,977 --> 00:44:07,311
Oh, come on.

879
00:44:07,311 --> 00:44:09,780
[It Tastes Better If You Use Your Hands]

880
00:44:09,780 --> 00:44:12,250
Would the kids want to hang out with us?

881
00:44:12,250 --> 00:44:13,818
We embarrass them.

882
00:44:13,818 --> 00:44:16,454
It's nice hanging out just us.

883
00:44:16,454 --> 00:44:18,422
Who cares if we're embarrassing?

884
00:44:18,422 --> 00:44:21,292
[There's Nothing Better
Than Friends Who Get You]

885
00:44:21,292 --> 00:44:25,096
I like that she broke them apart
with her hands.

886
00:44:25,096 --> 00:44:26,164
Does it taste okay?

887
00:44:26,164 --> 00:44:27,665
- Yes.
- It's tasty.

888
00:44:27,665 --> 00:44:28,699
Thank you.

889
00:44:28,699 --> 00:44:30,368
- One more sesame bread.
- Doesn't the croissant taste good?

890
00:44:30,368 --> 00:44:32,069
- Can we have one Black <i>Sigeumja</i> bread?
- Yes.

891
00:44:32,069 --> 00:44:35,139
- Black <i>Sieumjang</i> bread?
- Yes.

892
00:44:35,139 --> 00:44:36,140
That's...

893
00:44:36,140 --> 00:44:38,109
<i>- Sieumjang...</i>
- What's the one with the black filling?

894
00:44:38,109 --> 00:44:39,977
- Black filling?
- Yes.

895
00:44:39,977 --> 00:44:41,345
<i>- Sigeumja.</i>
- Sesame.

896
00:44:41,345 --> 00:44:43,080
- Oh, the black sesame.
- Yes.

897
00:44:43,080 --> 00:44:45,049
[&lt;I&gt;Sigeumja&lt;/I&gt; Is The Regional Word For Sesame]
Coming right up.

898
00:44:45,049 --> 00:44:47,652
- This is what it looks like.
- So...

899
00:44:47,652 --> 00:44:48,653
[Black Sesame Flan]
It looks fancy.

900
00:44:48,653 --> 00:44:51,489
- I've never had anything like it.
- <i>Sigeumja</i> bread.

901
00:44:51,489 --> 00:44:55,059
We're all the same.
None of us has tried them.

902
00:44:55,059 --> 00:44:56,294
[She's Back At It Again]
It's good.

903
00:44:56,294 --> 00:44:58,896
[Cutting Them Into 4 Equal Portions]

904
00:44:58,896 --> 00:45:01,465
Aren't you supposed to scoop it like this
instead of cutting it?

905
00:45:01,465 --> 00:45:03,367
Yeah, it seems like it.

906
00:45:03,367 --> 00:45:05,002
- I think you're right.
- Yes.

907
00:45:06,070 --> 00:45:07,571
It's so tasty.

908
00:45:09,340 --> 00:45:10,274
Right?

909
00:45:10,274 --> 00:45:12,643
How is it so delicious?

910
00:45:13,544 --> 00:45:16,280
[They're Happy To Eat It As Is]
How is it so delicious?

911
00:45:16,280 --> 00:45:19,317
[But She Needs To Divide It Equally]
It's so good.

912
00:45:19,317 --> 00:45:21,786
I don't think you're meant to cut it.

913
00:45:21,786 --> 00:45:23,721
This is how you eat it.

914
00:45:23,721 --> 00:45:25,723
You're going to a lot of trouble
just to cut it into four.

915
00:45:25,723 --> 00:45:27,091
All done.

916
00:45:31,095 --> 00:45:34,832
[Scraping Up Every Last Bit]
It's chewy like a rice cake.

917
00:45:34,832 --> 00:45:39,670
Who scrapes a cup of coffee like that?

918
00:45:39,670 --> 00:45:41,172
She's scraping away.

919
00:45:41,172 --> 00:45:43,507
[Encore Performance]

920
00:45:43,507 --> 00:45:46,477
She doesn't want to let
a single drop go to waste.

921
00:45:46,477 --> 00:45:49,213
We left quite a mess,

922
00:45:49,213 --> 00:45:52,316
- with all that ripping.
- Yes.

923
00:45:52,316 --> 00:45:54,585
[The Aftermath Of The Quartering]

924
00:45:54,585 --> 00:45:56,854
[Customers Are Waiting In Line]
I don't know enough to order.

925
00:45:56,854 --> 00:45:58,923
Hello, Gi Ho Bong?

926
00:45:58,923 --> 00:45:59,824
- Yes!
- Yes.

927
00:45:59,824 --> 00:46:01,792
Come on in.

928
00:46:02,693 --> 00:46:04,428
[The First Party On The Waitlist Enters]
Hello.

929
00:46:04,428 --> 00:46:05,763
- Hello.
- How many people?

930
00:46:05,763 --> 00:46:07,498
- Three people.
- You're a party of three?

931
00:46:07,498 --> 00:46:09,200
Hyun Seon Ja?

932
00:46:09,200 --> 00:46:10,101
- Yes.
- Yes.

933
00:46:10,101 --> 00:46:11,235
[The Second Party Enters]
Hello.

934
00:46:11,235 --> 00:46:12,870
- Hello.
- You came again!

935
00:46:12,870 --> 00:46:14,839
We need to take a new photo.
You blinked the last time.

936
00:46:14,839 --> 00:46:16,407
- My eyes were closed?
- Yes.

937
00:46:16,407 --> 00:46:18,409
That's so unlike me.

938
00:46:18,409 --> 00:46:19,710
- Sit over there.
- Where?

939
00:46:20,745 --> 00:46:21,779
[The New Customers Are Seated Side By Side]

940
00:46:21,779 --> 00:46:23,180
I'm going to have a cup of tea as well.

941
00:46:23,180 --> 00:46:24,849
- My goodness.
- What?

942
00:46:24,849 --> 00:46:25,983
[Customers Have Arrived]

943
00:46:25,983 --> 00:46:27,318
[Must Check Id]
Should we check their IDs?

944
00:46:27,318 --> 00:46:30,688
- No need. They've been here before.
- I see.

945
00:46:31,689 --> 00:46:34,692
[Gi Ho Jik (3rd Visit)
Hyun Seon Ja (2nd Visit)]

946
00:46:34,692 --> 00:46:36,827
[Seon Ho's Regular Customer, Mr. Gi Ho Jik]
Of course.

947
00:46:36,827 --> 00:46:38,262
Are you closed tomorrow?

948
00:46:38,262 --> 00:46:40,765
Yes, we're closed.
We'll be back next week.

949
00:46:40,765 --> 00:46:42,800
- Next week?
- Yes, please come then.

950
00:46:43,601 --> 00:46:45,736
Okay, I'll come visit all the time.

951
00:46:45,736 --> 00:46:47,905
[He Promised Seon Ho He Would Come Again]

952
00:46:47,905 --> 00:46:51,042
[Even Though Seon Ho's Not Here
He Kept His Promise]

953
00:46:51,042 --> 00:46:54,412
- Mom.
- That fellow was here last time, too.

954
00:46:54,412 --> 00:46:57,047
[Another Customer Who Seems Familiar]

955
00:46:58,316 --> 00:47:01,218
[Gi Ho Bong, Village Head]
[He Had A Taste Of Desserts Before Opening]

956
00:47:01,218 --> 00:47:02,420
- How is it?
- It's delicious.

957
00:47:02,420 --> 00:47:04,622
- You like it?
- Yes, it's good.

958
00:47:05,289 --> 00:47:08,693
[This Time, He Came With His Family]

959
00:47:08,693 --> 00:47:09,694
We see each other every day.

960
00:47:09,694 --> 00:47:13,263
- I tried the coffee last week.
- All right.

961
00:47:13,798 --> 00:47:17,401
[Regulars Who Feel Right At Home]

962
00:47:18,302 --> 00:47:21,038
[Here Comes Another Regular Customer]

963
00:47:24,842 --> 00:47:26,043
- You're back.
- Yes.

964
00:47:26,043 --> 00:47:27,344
Goodness.

965
00:47:27,878 --> 00:47:31,315
[Kim Sun Ja]
[Bonjour Bakery VVIP]

966
00:47:31,916 --> 00:47:32,983
- Take a seat.
- Sit here.

967
00:47:32,983 --> 00:47:36,554
[Neighbors Casually Coming Together]

968
00:47:36,554 --> 00:47:38,689
Ma'am, can I move this aside for a moment?

969
00:47:38,689 --> 00:47:40,558
Yes, put it outside.

970
00:47:40,558 --> 00:47:41,892
- I'll leave it here.
- Okay.

971
00:47:41,892 --> 00:47:43,394
It's right behind you.

972
00:47:45,763 --> 00:47:47,298
[Cha Chef Spies On The Hall]

973
00:47:47,298 --> 00:47:50,067
- Hello.
- Hello.

974
00:47:50,067 --> 00:47:53,104
- Hello.
- Hello.

975
00:47:53,104 --> 00:47:55,906
Hello again, sir.

976
00:47:55,906 --> 00:47:57,174
Mr. Cha Seung Won.

977
00:47:57,174 --> 00:47:58,976
You could start your own baking business.

978
00:47:58,976 --> 00:48:00,611
If you open your own shop,

979
00:48:00,611 --> 00:48:02,213
tell me the address
and I'll be there right away.

980
00:48:02,213 --> 00:48:04,915
I'll go anywhere in the country.

981
00:48:04,915 --> 00:48:07,385
[Grateful Just To Hear That]

982
00:48:07,385 --> 00:48:10,488
- Did you order a Cherry Blossom Tart?
- Yes.

983
00:48:10,488 --> 00:48:12,122
One Cherry Blossom Tart.

984
00:48:13,691 --> 00:48:15,493
- My goodness.
- One Cherry Blossom Tart.

985
00:48:15,493 --> 00:48:18,262
It looked big in the picture,
but it's tiny in real life.

986
00:48:18,262 --> 00:48:20,097
That's how it usually goes.

987
00:48:20,097 --> 00:48:23,167
That's how advertising works.

988
00:48:23,167 --> 00:48:24,468
If we make these big,

989
00:48:24,468 --> 00:48:26,003
there won't be a profit margin.

990
00:48:26,003 --> 00:48:28,005
You'll end up ruined.

991
00:48:28,005 --> 00:48:31,175
[I Was Just Teasing]

992
00:48:31,175 --> 00:48:33,277
[Shall We Dig In?]

993
00:48:33,277 --> 00:48:35,679
[Let's See How It Tastes]

994
00:48:35,679 --> 00:48:36,747
You cut it like this, right?

995
00:48:36,747 --> 00:48:39,884
Yes, you need to cut it up and eat it.

996
00:48:39,884 --> 00:48:41,719
[Chef Cha's Tip]
Make sure you eat them together.

997
00:48:41,719 --> 00:48:43,220
[Eat The Petals With The Cream]
Have this with that.

998
00:48:43,220 --> 00:48:44,688
Eat them together.

999
00:48:47,358 --> 00:48:50,161
[They Eat The Petals
As Instructed By Cha Chef]

1000
00:48:50,161 --> 00:48:52,663
It's very chewy.

1001
00:48:52,663 --> 00:48:54,698
[Meanwhile, At The Next Table]

1002
00:48:54,698 --> 00:48:57,435
This works as dinner tonight.

1003
00:48:57,435 --> 00:48:59,503
This is hardly enough.

1004
00:48:59,503 --> 00:49:02,973
I'm full. This is plenty.

1005
00:49:02,973 --> 00:49:05,309
You'll get rich soon

1006
00:49:05,309 --> 00:49:09,213
if you can get by eating so little.

1007
00:49:09,213 --> 00:49:13,350
[Yes, I Plan To Get Very Rich]

1008
00:49:13,350 --> 00:49:15,886
Where are the dish sponges?

1009
00:49:15,886 --> 00:49:18,022
Are there none left?

1010
00:49:18,022 --> 00:49:19,457
I didn't see one.

1011
00:49:19,457 --> 00:49:21,559
Go and look in the sink.

1012
00:49:21,559 --> 00:49:23,961
- Inside the sink?
- Yes.

1013
00:49:23,961 --> 00:49:25,463
I need to clean the plates.

1014
00:49:25,463 --> 00:49:28,599
I have to go do the dishes.

1015
00:49:28,599 --> 00:49:33,103
He always makes the effort.

1016
00:49:33,103 --> 00:49:34,839
He does the dishes in our house.

1017
00:49:34,839 --> 00:49:36,807
Yeah, I heard.

1018
00:49:36,807 --> 00:49:39,410
I didn't think he'd lift a finger.

1019
00:49:39,410 --> 00:49:41,078
I was surprised as well.

1020
00:49:41,078 --> 00:49:43,080
Yeah, I guess people change.

1021
00:49:43,080 --> 00:49:45,649
Now that we're older,

1022
00:49:45,649 --> 00:49:48,586
he's a changed person.

1023
00:49:48,586 --> 00:49:52,389
It's time for him to change his ways.

1024
00:49:52,389 --> 00:49:53,891
[A Father And Son On Their First Visit]

1025
00:49:53,891 --> 00:49:56,760
[Cho Bang Hun, Cho Byeong Gyu]

1026
00:49:56,760 --> 00:49:58,095
As for coffee...

1027
00:49:58,095 --> 00:49:59,730
- Not for me.
- You don't drink them, right?

1028
00:50:00,798 --> 00:50:03,734
[What Else Is There?]

1029
00:50:04,335 --> 00:50:05,769
[Awkward Father]

1030
00:50:05,769 --> 00:50:08,572
[Awkward Son]

1031
00:50:08,572 --> 00:50:10,841
[He Just Keeps Awkwardly Rubbing His Face]

1032
00:50:14,345 --> 00:50:16,947
I've come to Sillim with Byeong Gyu.

1033
00:50:16,947 --> 00:50:18,449
[A Sudden Phone Call]

1034
00:50:18,449 --> 00:50:19,850
Sillim.

1035
00:50:19,850 --> 00:50:21,752
We're at some bakery.

1036
00:50:21,752 --> 00:50:23,821
- I'll be there later.
<i>- Okay.</i>

1037
00:50:23,821 --> 00:50:25,823
- Excuse me.
- Are you ready to order?

1038
00:50:25,823 --> 00:50:28,926
- Okay.
- We'll have two flans and one tart.

1039
00:50:28,926 --> 00:50:30,361
[That's A Lot For Two People]
Two Black Sesame Flans?

1040
00:50:30,361 --> 00:50:31,529
This one...

1041
00:50:31,529 --> 00:50:32,997
Do you want to try one first?

1042
00:50:32,997 --> 00:50:35,599
- Sure.
- Okay, one flan and one tart.

1043
00:50:35,599 --> 00:50:38,602
- Are you father and son?
- Yes.

1044
00:50:38,602 --> 00:50:40,571
It's nice to see.

1045
00:50:40,571 --> 00:50:42,372
I'll take the menus.

1046
00:50:43,774 --> 00:50:47,177
[A Slightly Awkward Father-And-Son Date]

1047
00:50:47,177 --> 00:50:48,746
- They're ready to go.
- Okay.

1048
00:50:48,746 --> 00:50:51,482
[To Ease The Awkwardness]

1049
00:50:51,482 --> 00:50:52,917
[Here Are Some Sweet Desserts]
Here you go.

1050
00:50:52,917 --> 00:50:55,152
- Hello.
- Thank you.

1051
00:50:56,820 --> 00:50:58,956
- Go ahead and try it.
- Okay.

1052
00:51:03,961 --> 00:51:05,663
- Is it okay?
- What is this?

1053
00:51:05,663 --> 00:51:06,830
[He Takes His Phone Back Out]

1054
00:51:06,830 --> 00:51:09,566
- It's lemon tea.
- Try it.

1055
00:51:12,102 --> 00:51:13,604
[Click]

1056
00:51:14,672 --> 00:51:17,341
[A Photo Keepsake Of Their Time Together]

1057
00:51:19,143 --> 00:51:22,046
<i>My father lives alone.</i>

1058
00:51:22,046 --> 00:51:27,184
<i>I brought him here for bread and coffee.</i>

1059
00:51:27,184 --> 00:51:30,354
We didn't go out much together
while my mother was alive.

1060
00:51:30,354 --> 00:51:33,023
[After His Mother Passed Away]
But now that my father is alone,

1061
00:51:33,023 --> 00:51:37,094
[He Started Caring More For His Father]
I try to take him out more.

1062
00:51:39,396 --> 00:51:41,065
Just in case you're interested...

1063
00:51:41,065 --> 00:51:44,401
These are descriptions
of the desserts you ordered.

1064
00:51:44,401 --> 00:51:46,003
- Have a read.
- Thank you.

1065
00:51:46,003 --> 00:51:47,504
What is this?

1066
00:51:48,505 --> 00:51:51,175
- It's the desserts we just ate.
- Right.

1067
00:51:51,175 --> 00:51:54,244
I'll show this off tomorrow.

1068
00:51:54,244 --> 00:51:57,748
There'll be lots of people
at the Senior Community Center.

1069
00:51:57,748 --> 00:52:00,617
I'll tell everyone
I went to Bonjour Bakery.

1070
00:52:01,385 --> 00:52:03,354
Thank you.

1071
00:52:03,354 --> 00:52:04,855
It hit me one day

1072
00:52:04,855 --> 00:52:07,024
just how quickly time passes.

1073
00:52:07,024 --> 00:52:08,859
Our time is so fleeting.

1074
00:52:08,859 --> 00:52:11,462
I thought about that a lot.

1075
00:52:11,462 --> 00:52:15,633
I try to spend as much time
with him as possible.

1076
00:52:15,633 --> 00:52:17,868
But it's not as easy as it seems.

1077
00:52:21,305 --> 00:52:24,274
Let's go this way.

1078
00:52:29,013 --> 00:52:32,049
[We Are Open]

1079
00:52:40,090 --> 00:52:45,295
[May This Visit Be Etched In Your Hearts]

1080
00:52:45,295 --> 00:52:48,999
[The Next Morning]

1081
00:52:57,708 --> 00:53:02,412
[Seon Ho Got Back Late Last Night
After His Performance]

1082
00:53:07,918 --> 00:53:10,287
This mountain view is incredible.

1083
00:53:13,590 --> 00:53:18,161
[Zoning Out]

1084
00:53:18,896 --> 00:53:21,298
- Did you sleep well?
- Yeah.

1085
00:53:21,298 --> 00:53:24,034
We'd better head in to work, Seon Ho.

1086
00:53:24,868 --> 00:53:27,905
Hello.

1087
00:53:27,905 --> 00:53:29,106
Hello.

1088
00:53:29,106 --> 00:53:32,242
We run a bakery café over there.

1089
00:53:32,242 --> 00:53:33,544
- I know.
- You do?

1090
00:53:33,544 --> 00:53:34,745
I went yesterday.

1091
00:53:34,745 --> 00:53:36,647
- Did you?
- I wasn't there yesterday.

1092
00:53:36,647 --> 00:53:38,615
So you should come again today.

1093
00:53:38,615 --> 00:53:40,517
All right.

1094
00:53:40,517 --> 00:53:42,419
- Where are you headed?
- I'm going to work.

1095
00:53:42,419 --> 00:53:44,722
Really? We're headed the same way.

1096
00:53:44,722 --> 00:53:46,857
The weather is so nice today.

1097
00:53:46,857 --> 00:53:48,092
It's lovely.

1098
00:53:48,092 --> 00:53:49,560
It's so nice here.

1099
00:53:49,560 --> 00:53:53,097
<i>I love seeing this view</i>
<i>first thing in the morning.</i>

1100
00:53:53,097 --> 00:53:54,565
<i>And it's so quiet.</i>

1101
00:53:54,565 --> 00:53:55,733
Which way are you going?

1102
00:53:55,733 --> 00:53:57,234
- That way.
- Over there?

1103
00:53:57,234 --> 00:53:58,869
- We're this way, right?
- Off you go.

1104
00:53:58,869 --> 00:54:00,137
- All right.
- Yes, we're this way.

1105
00:54:00,137 --> 00:54:01,472
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

1106
00:54:01,472 --> 00:54:03,407
- See you later, ma'am. Have a great day!
- Bye.

1107
00:54:03,407 --> 00:54:05,976
- Have a nice day.
- Okay.

1108
00:54:05,976 --> 00:54:08,212
Let's start the day with a cup of coffee.

1109
00:54:08,212 --> 00:54:10,848
- Do you want an egg?
- I'd love one.

1110
00:54:10,848 --> 00:54:12,583
- How about a tomato and blueberry drink?
- Okay.

1111
00:54:12,583 --> 00:54:14,852
You get on that while I make the coffee.

1112
00:54:14,852 --> 00:54:15,786
All right.

1113
00:54:15,786 --> 00:54:19,256
[Ki Taek Lights Up At The Idea
Of Feeding Seon Ho]

1114
00:54:19,256 --> 00:54:21,892
[Meanwhile, The Manager Is Out For A Stroll]

1115
00:54:21,892 --> 00:54:24,795
Spring is really...

1116
00:54:24,795 --> 00:54:26,830
It's such an elegant season.

1117
00:54:26,830 --> 00:54:28,432
It's so short.

1118
00:54:28,432 --> 00:54:31,168
It's not a good deal.

1119
00:54:31,168 --> 00:54:32,302
[To Make The Most Of It]

1120
00:54:32,302 --> 00:54:34,505
You need to enjoy it to the fullest.

1121
00:54:34,505 --> 00:54:37,374
[Manager Hee Ae Gets An Early Start]

1122
00:54:38,308 --> 00:54:41,278
[Spring Has Come To Gochang]

1123
00:54:42,613 --> 00:54:46,250
[Hee Ae Follows The Spring Breeze]

1124
00:54:46,250 --> 00:54:49,052
This fresh breeze

1125
00:54:49,052 --> 00:54:52,355
won't last very long, which is a shame.

1126
00:54:55,425 --> 00:54:58,195
It's so refreshing.

1127
00:54:58,195 --> 00:55:00,163
Look, they're so cute.

1128
00:55:04,902 --> 00:55:08,071
I wonder what's on the other side.

1129
00:55:08,071 --> 00:55:10,741
Let's check it out.

1130
00:55:10,741 --> 00:55:12,576
- What on earth?
- Hold on.

1131
00:55:12,576 --> 00:55:14,511
[An Unexpected Cliff]
But I... This path...

1132
00:55:14,511 --> 00:55:16,647
Oh, you have to follow this path...

1133
00:55:16,647 --> 00:55:19,049
Should we walk up just a little?

1134
00:55:20,284 --> 00:55:23,386
[I, Hee Ae, Am Not Easily Thrown
And I Will Continue To Venture Upward]

1135
00:55:24,488 --> 00:55:26,723
[One Step At A Time]

1136
00:55:26,723 --> 00:55:30,694
[And Another Bigger Step]

1137
00:55:30,694 --> 00:55:32,296
It's nice.

1138
00:55:32,296 --> 00:55:35,999
[Every Ending Is A New Beginning]

1139
00:55:37,000 --> 00:55:39,903
[If You Take The Unexpected Path]

1140
00:55:39,903 --> 00:55:42,372
This is so nice.

1141
00:55:42,372 --> 00:55:44,374
[You Might Discover A New World Of Spring]

1142
00:55:44,374 --> 00:55:47,177
This is exciting.

1143
00:55:47,177 --> 00:55:48,979
[And]

1144
00:55:51,048 --> 00:55:53,183
[A Surprising View]

1145
00:55:53,183 --> 00:55:55,485
This is such a surprise.

1146
00:55:59,022 --> 00:56:01,592
I didn't expect it to be so nice up here.

1147
00:56:01,592 --> 00:56:04,227
All I could think of was how steep it was.

1148
00:56:05,162 --> 00:56:06,396
What a lucky discovery.

1149
00:56:06,396 --> 00:56:08,298
[Will The Bakery Be Just As Lucky Today?]

1150
00:56:08,298 --> 00:56:10,600
This is amazing. It's insane.

1151
00:56:13,737 --> 00:56:15,706
[Gearing Up For Another Long Day]

1152
00:56:15,706 --> 00:56:18,842
[With A High-Energy Smoothie]

1153
00:56:23,380 --> 00:56:25,482
[He Compares The Volume]

1154
00:56:25,482 --> 00:56:27,884
[And Gives The Bigger Serving To Seon Ho]

1155
00:56:29,753 --> 00:56:31,488
- I filled it up with love.
- Ki Taek.

1156
00:56:31,488 --> 00:56:34,324
I really appreciate it.

1157
00:56:34,324 --> 00:56:35,259
It's filled with love.

1158
00:56:35,259 --> 00:56:38,028
I don't get drinks this healthy at home.

1159
00:56:38,028 --> 00:56:40,330
I get to eat this all thanks to you.

1160
00:56:40,330 --> 00:56:43,633
- Thanks for saying that.
- Thanks.

1161
00:56:49,172 --> 00:56:50,574
I think it's so tasty.

1162
00:56:50,574 --> 00:56:52,075
- You like it?
- Yeah.

1163
00:56:52,075 --> 00:56:53,810
I'm so happy to hear that.

1164
00:56:53,810 --> 00:56:55,479
It's really tasty.

1165
00:56:55,479 --> 00:56:59,583
- Thanks, Seon Ho.
- I should be thanking you.

1166
00:57:05,889 --> 00:57:08,425
I washed my hands.

1167
00:57:08,425 --> 00:57:10,060
[An Egg Peeled With Love]

1168
00:57:10,060 --> 00:57:12,996
- Oh, you peeled it?
- Yeah.

1169
00:57:12,996 --> 00:57:15,465
The shell cracked,
so I just peeled it off.

1170
00:57:17,834 --> 00:57:21,371
How did you get the yolk so perfectly?

1171
00:57:22,139 --> 00:57:24,074
It's impressive.

1172
00:57:24,074 --> 00:57:28,445
[High Off The Praise, He Hums Happily]

1173
00:57:33,717 --> 00:57:35,418
The ice just slides in,

1174
00:57:36,987 --> 00:57:38,956
thanks to the wide neck.

1175
00:57:38,956 --> 00:57:41,558
It's so easy to fill.

1176
00:57:41,558 --> 00:57:43,160
[It Maintains Temperature Well]
<i>It's so well insulated.</i>

1177
00:57:43,160 --> 00:57:45,895
[Which Is Perfect For Trips]
<i>I'd better take one with me.</i>

1178
00:57:47,064 --> 00:57:48,632
I'm so excited.

1179
00:57:48,632 --> 00:57:50,701
- I can't wait to go to the market.
- Listen.

1180
00:57:50,701 --> 00:57:53,036
- Compared to other types of shopping--
- It is so much fun.

1181
00:57:53,036 --> 00:57:54,705
I guarantee that a trip to the market

1182
00:57:54,705 --> 00:57:57,908
is one thing you definitely won't regret.

1183
00:57:57,908 --> 00:58:00,644
It gets your heart racing.

1184
00:58:00,644 --> 00:58:02,879
- Hello!
- Can I get a cup of coffee?

1185
00:58:02,879 --> 00:58:04,614
- Cold or hot?
- Cold.

1186
00:58:04,614 --> 00:58:06,650
One iced Americano.

1187
00:58:06,650 --> 00:58:08,752
- Doesn't he look stylish today?
- Yeah.

1188
00:58:08,752 --> 00:58:10,320
He really does.

1189
00:58:24,701 --> 00:58:26,836
My goodness.

1190
00:58:34,378 --> 00:58:37,514
[Perfect Weather
For Gazing At The Green Barley Field]

1191
00:58:37,514 --> 00:58:41,418
[While Enjoying An Iced Americano]

1192
00:58:43,186 --> 00:58:45,255
Gosh, Seung Won.

1193
00:58:45,255 --> 00:58:48,358
You look so cool.

1194
00:58:48,358 --> 00:58:51,028
[Seon Ho Waters The Plants]
You need to enjoy these moments.

1195
00:58:51,028 --> 00:58:53,296
- That view over there is like a poster.
- Yes.

1196
00:58:53,296 --> 00:58:54,564
- It is.
- It's a poster.

1197
00:58:54,564 --> 00:58:56,266
- It's picture perfect.
- All of this together...

1198
00:58:56,266 --> 00:58:58,235
We complete the picture.

1199
00:58:58,235 --> 00:58:59,803
[We're The Poster]

1200
00:58:59,803 --> 00:59:01,705
We're the main attraction.

1201
00:59:03,640 --> 00:59:05,542
- Ki Taek.
- Yes?

1202
00:59:05,542 --> 00:59:07,778
- If anyone steals this jacket,
- Yes?

1203
00:59:07,778 --> 00:59:09,112
I'll kill them.

1204
00:59:09,112 --> 00:59:11,014
- Okay, I'll take good care of it.
- Okay.

1205
00:59:11,581 --> 00:59:13,850
- Can I try it on just once?
- Of course.

1206
00:59:13,850 --> 00:59:16,086
[I'll Take Good Care Of It]
It's just so nice.

1207
00:59:16,086 --> 00:59:17,187
[After I Try It On]
Try it on.

1208
00:59:17,187 --> 00:59:18,789
Gosh, it's really...

1209
00:59:18,789 --> 00:59:19,689
It looks good.

1210
00:59:19,689 --> 00:59:21,358
It's such a nice fit.

1211
00:59:21,358 --> 00:59:22,426
What a killer design.

1212
00:59:22,426 --> 00:59:24,627
Where's the mirror?

1213
00:59:25,462 --> 00:59:27,731
What do we need to buy today?

1214
00:59:27,731 --> 00:59:30,300
- Spam.
- Just spam and dried seaweed?

1215
00:59:30,300 --> 00:59:32,402
- Yes, spam and dried seaweed.
- Okay.

1216
00:59:32,402 --> 00:59:33,804
And two bags of bean sprouts.

1217
00:59:33,804 --> 00:59:35,238
- Two bags?
- Yes, two bags.

1218
00:59:35,238 --> 00:59:36,807
We should carry one bag each.

1219
00:59:36,807 --> 00:59:38,375
- Let's go.
- Okay.

1220
00:59:39,409 --> 00:59:41,611
That van suits you so well.

1221
00:59:41,611 --> 00:59:44,247
- That van?
- Yes.

1222
00:59:44,247 --> 00:59:45,582
Shall we set out?

1223
00:59:45,582 --> 00:59:47,651
- Let's go!
- Okay.

1224
00:59:47,651 --> 00:59:49,786
[Off To The Market]

1225
00:59:49,786 --> 00:59:52,422
Don't be shocked
when you get to the market.

1226
00:59:52,422 --> 00:59:53,356
Do they go crazy over you?

1227
00:59:53,356 --> 00:59:55,025
Not me.

1228
00:59:55,025 --> 00:59:57,561
- They all recognized Hee Ae.
- Right.

1229
00:59:57,561 --> 00:59:59,362
But not one single person

1230
00:59:59,362 --> 01:00:00,597
knew who I was.

1231
01:00:00,597 --> 01:00:02,833
But people at the bakery love you.

1232
01:00:02,833 --> 01:00:04,501
They do like me,

1233
01:00:04,501 --> 01:00:07,237
but it's because they come
with their daughters or granddaughters,

1234
01:00:07,237 --> 01:00:09,539
and they know who I am.

1235
01:00:09,539 --> 01:00:11,675
I seem familiar to the seniors.

1236
01:00:11,675 --> 01:00:14,244
But Hee Ae is obviously

1237
01:00:14,244 --> 01:00:16,780
- so famous even among older people.
- Yes.

1238
01:00:16,780 --> 01:00:18,915
They approach her comfortably.

1239
01:00:18,915 --> 01:00:20,851
They went mad for her at the market.

1240
01:00:20,851 --> 01:00:23,320
The wide opening makes it
so easy to drink even while driving.

1241
01:00:23,320 --> 01:00:27,257
[It's Easy To Drink From It
Because Of Its Wide Opening]

1242
01:00:27,257 --> 01:00:28,325
That's so refreshing.

1243
01:00:28,325 --> 01:00:31,394
Thanks.

1244
01:00:32,529 --> 01:00:34,431
Where is it? There it is.

1245
01:00:34,431 --> 01:00:35,632
We're here.

1246
01:00:35,632 --> 01:00:37,033
[Gochang Traditional Market]

1247
01:00:37,033 --> 01:00:39,102
Take a look at this.

1248
01:00:39,102 --> 01:00:42,873
You won't find dried yellow croaker
and Donald Duck anywhere else like this.

1249
01:00:42,873 --> 01:00:44,007
What a lovely set.

1250
01:00:44,007 --> 01:00:46,943
This is the charm of this market.
Isn't that right, ma'am?

1251
01:00:46,943 --> 01:00:48,812
By the way, who are you again?

1252
01:00:48,812 --> 01:00:50,180
- I am...
- Yes?

1253
01:00:50,180 --> 01:00:53,316
- Did you ever see <i>2 Days &amp; 1 Night</i>?
- Thank you.

1254
01:00:53,316 --> 01:00:54,918
One of the members is called Kim Seon Ho.

1255
01:00:54,918 --> 01:00:56,486
[Sudden Self-Introduction Time]
I'm him.

1256
01:00:56,486 --> 01:00:58,555
I was also in a drama called
<i>Hometown Cha-Cha-Cha</i>.

1257
01:00:58,555 --> 01:00:59,489
I saw that drama.

1258
01:00:59,489 --> 01:01:00,490
That's me.

1259
01:01:00,490 --> 01:01:02,659
- I was Chief Hong.
- Chief Hong.

1260
01:01:02,659 --> 01:01:04,294
- Did you not get that into it?
- Chief Hong?

1261
01:01:04,294 --> 01:01:05,562
- Yes, Chief Hong!
- Chief Hong!

1262
01:01:05,562 --> 01:01:07,063
I did get into it.

1263
01:01:07,063 --> 01:01:08,331
I played Chief Hong.

1264
01:01:08,932 --> 01:01:11,268
This one looks more familiar.

1265
01:01:11,268 --> 01:01:13,103
You don't recognize me...

1266
01:01:13,103 --> 01:01:16,473
Why does he look more familiar
when you saw my drama?

1267
01:01:16,473 --> 01:01:18,208
[I Can't Explain It]

1268
01:01:18,208 --> 01:01:20,110
I hope you sell out, ma'am.

1269
01:01:20,110 --> 01:01:22,378
Take care.

1270
01:01:24,281 --> 01:01:28,585
[Will Anyone At The Market
Recognize Seon Ho?]

1271
01:01:28,585 --> 01:01:31,054
Do you see that big sign over there?

1272
01:01:31,054 --> 01:01:32,522
Do you see the stall selling
twisted rice donuts?

1273
01:01:32,522 --> 01:01:34,457
- Is that where you got them?
- That's the place.

1274
01:01:34,457 --> 01:01:37,027
We need to hit up that stall.

1275
01:01:37,027 --> 01:01:39,062
- Hello.
- Hello.

1276
01:01:39,062 --> 01:01:40,564
This is the stall.

1277
01:01:40,564 --> 01:01:42,699
- Look at all this.
- Fish cakes, please.

1278
01:01:48,271 --> 01:01:49,839
Thank you.

1279
01:01:50,640 --> 01:01:52,209
I'm really enjoying your drama.

1280
01:01:52,209 --> 01:01:53,577
- Really?
- You've seen it?

1281
01:01:53,577 --> 01:01:55,478
[They Recognize Ki Taek First]
Have you seen his drama?

1282
01:01:55,478 --> 01:01:56,379
Of course.

1283
01:01:56,379 --> 01:01:58,181
- Isn't he a great actor?
- Yes.

1284
01:01:58,181 --> 01:02:00,517
It's a shame it airs after midnight.

1285
01:02:00,517 --> 01:02:02,652
[Chief Hong Is Also Fading Out Of The Frame]

1286
01:02:02,652 --> 01:02:05,422
Thanks for staying up to watch it.
It can't be easy.

1287
01:02:05,422 --> 01:02:07,057
Since I cut my hair,

1288
01:02:07,057 --> 01:02:09,593
I didn't think anyone would recognize me.

1289
01:02:09,593 --> 01:02:11,228
You're too handsome to forget.

1290
01:02:11,228 --> 01:02:12,529
You shine on the screen.

1291
01:02:12,529 --> 01:02:13,563
Thank you.

1292
01:02:13,563 --> 01:02:15,999
[Seon Ho Is Happy To See Ki Taek Get Credit]
He used to be a model.

1293
01:02:15,999 --> 01:02:17,300
He's strikingly attractive.

1294
01:02:22,572 --> 01:02:24,040
After you finish...

1295
01:02:24,674 --> 01:02:25,842
They've got bean sprouts.

1296
01:02:25,842 --> 01:02:28,011
Hello.

1297
01:02:28,011 --> 01:02:28,945
Well, aren't you handsome?

1298
01:02:28,945 --> 01:02:30,947
- We need some bean sprouts.
- Okay.

1299
01:02:30,947 --> 01:02:33,116
Can we get two bags of fresh bean sprouts?

1300
01:02:33,116 --> 01:02:35,719
- It's for Seung Won.
- Of course.

1301
01:02:35,719 --> 01:02:36,987
Is this the usual amount?

1302
01:02:36,987 --> 01:02:40,390
[Served With The Owner's Generous Touch]
I'm feeling generous toward handsome boys.

1303
01:02:40,390 --> 01:02:41,558
- Thank you.
- Sure.

1304
01:02:41,558 --> 01:02:43,793
Our café is called Bonjour Bakery.

1305
01:02:43,793 --> 01:02:45,895
Come by sometime.

1306
01:02:45,895 --> 01:02:47,831
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1307
01:02:47,831 --> 01:02:49,666
<i>Hometown Cha-Cha-Cha!</i>

1308
01:02:49,666 --> 01:02:51,534
Chief Hong!

1309
01:02:51,534 --> 01:02:53,336
Finally, someone recognizes me.

1310
01:02:53,336 --> 01:02:55,338
<i>Hometown Cha-Cha-Cha!</i>

1311
01:02:55,338 --> 01:02:57,707
- At last, I can rest easy.
- It's crazy they don't know.

1312
01:02:57,707 --> 01:02:58,975
No one else recognized me.

1313
01:02:58,975 --> 01:03:00,443
I watched that drama on repeat.

1314
01:03:00,443 --> 01:03:02,312
Finally.

1315
01:03:02,312 --> 01:03:04,114
<i>2 Days &amp; 1 Night!</i>

1316
01:03:04,114 --> 01:03:05,515
- I thought--
- This is crazy.

1317
01:03:05,515 --> 01:03:07,017
I was sad that no one recognized me.

1318
01:03:07,017 --> 01:03:09,152
I feel so much better now.

1319
01:03:09,152 --> 01:03:10,287
I'm happy now.

1320
01:03:10,287 --> 01:03:11,788
I can hold my head up high as your senior.

1321
01:03:11,788 --> 01:03:13,089
I feel happy on your behalf.

1322
01:03:13,089 --> 01:03:15,091
- Thanks, Ki Taek.
- Sure.

1323
01:03:15,091 --> 01:03:16,526
Let's quickly get the dried seaweed

1324
01:03:16,526 --> 01:03:18,995
- and get back before we get in trouble.
- We need to hurry.

1325
01:03:18,995 --> 01:03:20,063
[Let's Hurry Before We're Late!]

1326
01:03:20,063 --> 01:03:21,398
This is how you wipe a counter.

1327
01:03:21,398 --> 01:03:24,768
[While Chef Cha Waits For His Staff]

1328
01:03:24,768 --> 01:03:28,705
[Someone Makes Her Way To The Café]

1329
01:03:33,376 --> 01:03:34,944
There are trees.

1330
01:03:35,478 --> 01:03:38,648
[She's Already Bursting With Curiosity]

1331
01:03:38,648 --> 01:03:39,816
There it is.

1332
01:03:39,816 --> 01:03:42,919
[Today's New Part-Timer]

1333
01:03:43,486 --> 01:03:44,821
[She's A Chic City Girl]

1334
01:03:44,821 --> 01:03:47,891
[With A Gentle Grace To Boot]

1335
01:03:47,891 --> 01:03:50,160
[Actress Lee Joo Bin]

1336
01:03:50,160 --> 01:03:55,064
Bonjour Bakery!

1337
01:03:57,100 --> 01:03:59,002
Excuse me.

1338
01:03:59,002 --> 01:04:00,403
Hello?

1339
01:04:01,271 --> 01:04:03,306
Is anyone here?

1340
01:04:03,306 --> 01:04:04,808
Hello?

1341
01:04:04,808 --> 01:04:07,510
[Is There Anyone In The Hall?]

1342
01:04:07,510 --> 01:04:11,614
I'm coming in, if that's okay?

1343
01:04:17,120 --> 01:04:18,388
Hello!

1344
01:04:18,388 --> 01:04:20,790
[Startled]

1345
01:04:27,864 --> 01:04:29,666
Hello.

1346
01:04:30,467 --> 01:04:31,801
- Hey.
- Hello.

1347
01:04:31,801 --> 01:04:33,503
- I'm the new part-timer.
- Okay.

1348
01:04:33,503 --> 01:04:36,639
- It's a pleasure.
- Yeah.

1349
01:04:36,639 --> 01:04:40,243
[He's In Full Concentration Mode]

1350
01:04:40,243 --> 01:04:41,644
[They Greeted Each Other Yesterday]
Oh, I see.

1351
01:04:41,644 --> 01:04:44,214
Since there will be three of you...

1352
01:04:44,214 --> 01:04:46,816
I'm told she's a good worker.

1353
01:04:46,816 --> 01:04:49,519
I'd better do my best.

1354
01:04:51,721 --> 01:04:53,856
[Peeks Inside]
Seung Won.

1355
01:04:55,692 --> 01:04:57,860
- Can I look around?
- Sure.

1356
01:04:58,728 --> 01:05:00,897
- Are you wearing a curtain?
- Sorry?

1357
01:05:00,897 --> 01:05:02,999
Never mind.

1358
01:05:02,999 --> 01:05:05,301
- Is that a curtain or what?
- Oh, right.

1359
01:05:05,301 --> 01:05:06,202
This dress?

1360
01:05:06,202 --> 01:05:07,670
I'll take it off soon
since it looks like a curtain.

1361
01:05:07,670 --> 01:05:09,405
All right.

1362
01:05:11,608 --> 01:05:12,742
We made all these.

1363
01:05:12,742 --> 01:05:15,078
- You made them all?
- Yeah.

1364
01:05:15,078 --> 01:05:16,279
We're making this one today.

1365
01:05:16,279 --> 01:05:17,714
[Showing Off His Babies]

1366
01:05:17,714 --> 01:05:18,982
I want to try that one.

1367
01:05:18,982 --> 01:05:20,817
- Which one?
- The Camellia Tart.

1368
01:05:20,817 --> 01:05:22,218
- I'm curious.
- You know what?

1369
01:05:22,218 --> 01:05:25,488
Don't let her come into the kitchen.

1370
01:05:25,488 --> 01:05:28,391
If anyone comes in here to sneak a taste,

1371
01:05:28,391 --> 01:05:30,660
send them straight back out, okay?

1372
01:05:33,029 --> 01:05:34,931
Hello.

1373
01:05:35,899 --> 01:05:37,434
It's nice to see you.

1374
01:05:37,434 --> 01:05:38,902
Have you eaten?

1375
01:05:38,902 --> 01:05:41,070
I had some <i>gimbap</i>. How about you?

1376
01:05:42,705 --> 01:05:44,874
- Come on, Hee Ae.
- Good morning.

1377
01:05:44,874 --> 01:05:46,376
Wait a minute.

1378
01:05:46,376 --> 01:05:47,610
Let's do a style check.

1379
01:05:47,610 --> 01:05:48,812
You're looking great, yet again.

1380
01:05:48,812 --> 01:05:51,581
Coming from a stylish guy like you...

1381
01:05:51,581 --> 01:05:53,716
- I feel honored.
- You look great.

1382
01:05:53,716 --> 01:05:56,186
- See that?
- Check out the rolled cuffs.

1383
01:05:56,186 --> 01:05:57,420
[Rolled Cuffs For A Stylish Touch]
He's too much.

1384
01:05:57,420 --> 01:05:58,822
Hang on.

1385
01:05:58,822 --> 01:06:00,723
You said my dress looks like a curtain,

1386
01:06:00,723 --> 01:06:01,925
- but you're complimenting Hee Ae.
- I did say that.

1387
01:06:01,925 --> 01:06:03,426
It's because you're so pretty.

1388
01:06:03,426 --> 01:06:05,295
- He wants to keep you humble.
- That's not it.

1389
01:06:05,295 --> 01:06:06,362
I meant it.

1390
01:06:06,362 --> 01:06:07,464
It looks like a curtain.

1391
01:06:07,464 --> 01:06:08,531
I'd better take it off.

1392
01:06:08,531 --> 01:06:11,167
- Your style is on point today.
- You look stunning.

1393
01:06:11,167 --> 01:06:13,570
- Check out those shoes.
- It's nice to be complimented

1394
01:06:13,570 --> 01:06:15,705
- by such a pretty girl.
- But seriously,

1395
01:06:15,705 --> 01:06:18,341
- I love that color combo.
- My goodness.

1396
01:06:18,341 --> 01:06:20,210
Does he always do a style check?

1397
01:06:20,210 --> 01:06:22,178
It's just his way of cheering us up

1398
01:06:22,178 --> 01:06:23,613
when we have a busy day ahead of us.

1399
01:06:23,613 --> 01:06:24,848
- I see.
- I appreciate it.

1400
01:06:24,848 --> 01:06:27,450
- What are you looking for?
- I'm just seeing what we have.

1401
01:06:27,450 --> 01:06:28,718
What's this?

1402
01:06:28,718 --> 01:06:31,387
Did Ki Taek put this here?

1403
01:06:31,387 --> 01:06:32,455
Probably.

1404
01:06:32,455 --> 01:06:34,424
He probably got it for you.

1405
01:06:34,424 --> 01:06:36,292
- For me?
- Yeah.

1406
01:06:36,292 --> 01:06:38,294
- Probably.
- I'd better eat it, then.

1407
01:06:38,995 --> 01:06:39,896
[Ragù Cheese Salt Bread]

1408
01:06:39,896 --> 01:06:43,066
[With Anseong Beef Filling]
<i>Let's try it. Come quickly.</i>

1409
01:06:43,066 --> 01:06:46,603
[A Light, Savoury Treat
Made Of Domestically Grown Ingredients]

1410
01:06:46,603 --> 01:06:48,505
- It's good, right?
- Yes, I really wanted to try it.

1411
01:06:48,505 --> 01:06:50,507
- I was craving bread with coffee.
- Right?

1412
01:06:50,507 --> 01:06:53,176
You need to try it now.
You won't get a chance later.

1413
01:06:53,176 --> 01:06:54,644
- All right.
- Thank you for this.

1414
01:06:54,644 --> 01:06:56,546
- Apparently,
- Yes?

1415
01:06:56,546 --> 01:06:58,348
it's filled with beef from Anseong.

1416
01:06:58,348 --> 01:06:59,749
That's what I heard.

1417
01:06:59,749 --> 01:07:02,885
It's made of beef from Anseong.

1418
01:07:12,095 --> 01:07:14,397
It's so tasty.

1419
01:07:14,397 --> 01:07:18,801
[They're Back From The Market Just In Time]

1420
01:07:20,169 --> 01:07:23,206
They went in that van?

1421
01:07:24,874 --> 01:07:27,243
- How manly.
- Very cool.

1422
01:07:28,044 --> 01:07:30,112
That's a real man's vehicle.

1423
01:07:35,852 --> 01:07:37,320
Okay.

1424
01:07:38,087 --> 01:07:39,355
- Hello, Hee Ae.
- Hello.

1425
01:07:39,355 --> 01:07:40,423
Here come real men.

1426
01:07:40,423 --> 01:07:43,226
- Hello.
- Hello.

1427
01:07:43,793 --> 01:07:46,229
[Meanwhile, Chef Cha]

1428
01:07:46,930 --> 01:07:50,099
[Has Been Working
Without A Break All Morning]

1429
01:08:00,109 --> 01:08:02,378
Has Ki Taek jumped ship? That rascal.

1430
01:08:02,378 --> 01:08:05,648
I'm nearly done getting ready, Seung Won.

1431
01:08:05,648 --> 01:08:07,850
I'll be with you soon.

1432
01:08:10,053 --> 01:08:13,957
I should've kicked him out way earlier.

1433
01:08:13,957 --> 01:08:17,026
I guess he can't handle it.

1434
01:08:17,026 --> 01:08:21,297
Six of my disciples quit before him.

1435
01:08:21,297 --> 01:08:25,935
One even left the country.

1436
01:08:25,935 --> 01:08:31,040
[That Rascal Is Rushing
To Get Back Into The Kitchen]

1437
01:08:31,040 --> 01:08:32,442
[11 A.M.]
Do I hang it up front?

1438
01:08:32,442 --> 01:08:33,643
Yes, on the door.

1439
01:08:33,643 --> 01:08:34,911
Hee Ae, will you ring the bell?

1440
01:08:34,911 --> 01:08:36,446
She's not letting go of that corn.

1441
01:08:36,446 --> 01:08:38,080
Look at that grip.

1442
01:08:38,615 --> 01:08:40,082
I'm not finished with it yet.

1443
01:08:42,652 --> 01:08:44,053
- Hee Ae.
- I had no place to put them.

1444
01:08:44,053 --> 01:08:45,321
All right.

1445
01:08:47,924 --> 01:08:49,825
We're open!

1446
01:08:50,493 --> 01:08:51,461
Seon Ho.

1447
01:08:51,461 --> 01:08:52,662
- Yes?
- Where's Hee Ae?

1448
01:08:52,662 --> 01:08:54,964
These were freshly baked today.

1449
01:08:54,964 --> 01:08:57,300
It's a tasting sample.

1450
01:08:57,300 --> 01:08:59,469
It's a kouign-amann and mille-feuille.

1451
01:08:59,469 --> 01:09:02,205
[A Sample Of Today's Menu]

1452
01:09:02,205 --> 01:09:05,441
- This is a new item.
- Today's a really lucky day.

1453
01:09:05,441 --> 01:09:07,110
Try the kouign-amann first.

1454
01:09:07,110 --> 01:09:10,013
[Cherry Blossom Kouign-Amann]
Do you want one each?

1455
01:09:10,013 --> 01:09:11,748
- All right.
- It's not too sweet.

1456
01:09:11,748 --> 01:09:15,485
- It's very refreshing.
- This bakery knows what it's doing.

1457
01:09:15,485 --> 01:09:17,186
This place is a real gem.

1458
01:09:23,760 --> 01:09:26,295
It's delicious!

1459
01:09:26,295 --> 01:09:28,464
I really want others to try it.

1460
01:09:28,464 --> 01:09:29,465
[A Gift For Myself]

1461
01:09:29,465 --> 01:09:32,134
[Me Too]

1462
01:09:33,369 --> 01:09:35,471
[He Mumbled Something About It Being Tasty]

1463
01:09:36,706 --> 01:09:38,608
[Strawberry Vanilla Mille-Feuille]
I don't think I've tried this one.

1464
01:09:38,608 --> 01:09:40,176
I need to taste it.

1465
01:09:40,176 --> 01:09:41,544
Does it taste okay?

1466
01:09:52,221 --> 01:09:54,590
It's so good.

1467
01:09:54,590 --> 01:09:55,625
Right?

1468
01:09:55,625 --> 01:09:57,960
It's a masterpiece. Don't you think?

1469
01:09:57,960 --> 01:10:00,129
I feel so happy.

1470
01:10:00,129 --> 01:10:01,864
It's incredible.

1471
01:10:01,864 --> 01:10:03,266
[Even If I May Say So Myself]

1472
01:10:03,266 --> 01:10:04,967
It's crazy good.

1473
01:10:06,102 --> 01:10:09,238
[He Proudly Samples His Own Masterpiece]

1474
01:10:14,744 --> 01:10:16,646
I feel like we're at a buffet.

1475
01:10:16,646 --> 01:10:18,648
There's even corn on the cob.

1476
01:10:18,648 --> 01:10:20,149
This bakery offers
great employment benefits.

1477
01:10:20,149 --> 01:10:21,217
Seriously.

1478
01:10:21,217 --> 01:10:22,652
They say the quality of the food

1479
01:10:22,652 --> 01:10:25,688
affects how much you enjoy something.

1480
01:10:25,688 --> 01:10:28,591
The quality of the food here is top-class.

1481
01:10:32,895 --> 01:10:35,832
[That's How Delicious Today's Desserts Are]

1482
01:10:35,832 --> 01:10:37,333
Oh, man.

1483
01:10:38,301 --> 01:10:41,838
We don't have any customers today.

1484
01:10:41,838 --> 01:10:43,506
Where is everyone?

1485
01:10:43,506 --> 01:10:45,808
[Monday]
[11 A.M.]

1486
01:10:45,808 --> 01:10:46,876
[The Public Offices And Local Businesses]

1487
01:10:46,876 --> 01:10:49,712
[Reopen After The Weekend]

1488
01:10:49,712 --> 01:10:51,013
[Gapyeong]

1489
01:10:51,013 --> 01:10:54,117
[When Locals Head Out On Errands]

1490
01:10:54,117 --> 01:10:55,218
[There's No Sign Of Life]

1491
01:10:55,218 --> 01:10:59,288
[And The Village Is Eerily Quiet]

1492
01:11:00,223 --> 01:11:02,792
[The King Of Baking Is Anxious]

1493
01:11:03,659 --> 01:11:05,828
[Swaying Slightly]
I checked. No one's lining up.

1494
01:11:05,828 --> 01:11:08,331
- What's going on?
- Yesterday was unexpectedly...

1495
01:11:08,331 --> 01:11:10,500
Hey!

1496
01:11:10,500 --> 01:11:13,202
[There's A Bakery Here]
Hey!

1497
01:11:16,239 --> 01:11:17,473
Where is everyone?

1498
01:11:17,473 --> 01:11:19,142
[Someone Is Here]

1499
01:11:19,142 --> 01:11:20,176
Hello.

1500
01:11:20,176 --> 01:11:21,144
Welcome!

1501
01:11:21,144 --> 01:11:23,146
- Hello.
- Hello.

1502
01:11:23,146 --> 01:11:24,647
[Pyo Ok Rye]
You came again.

1503
01:11:24,647 --> 01:11:27,283
You were here just yesterday.

1504
01:11:27,283 --> 01:11:28,718
Oh, did you bring the kimchi?

1505
01:11:28,718 --> 01:11:31,320
- Thank you.
- I'm not sure it's any good.

1506
01:11:31,320 --> 01:11:33,222
- Enjoy.
- Thank you so much.

1507
01:11:33,222 --> 01:11:34,190
- Thank you.
- You're just leaving?

1508
01:11:34,190 --> 01:11:35,725
- Should I wrap up some bread for you?
- No.

1509
01:11:35,725 --> 01:11:36,726
- Why not?
- I'll come back.

1510
01:11:36,726 --> 01:11:38,227
I had some yesterday.

1511
01:11:38,227 --> 01:11:40,129
- What about coffee?
- I'm fine.

1512
01:11:40,129 --> 01:11:41,063
Where are you going?

1513
01:11:41,063 --> 01:11:42,431
- I'm going home.
- Home?

1514
01:11:42,431 --> 01:11:43,833
- We'll go with you.
- We'll go with you.

1515
01:11:43,833 --> 01:11:46,068
[Clingy]

1516
01:11:46,068 --> 01:11:47,970
Where are you going?
Have a cup of coffee with us.

1517
01:11:47,970 --> 01:11:49,071
I don't want anything.

1518
01:11:49,071 --> 01:11:50,807
- How about a baked good?
- No, thanks.

1519
01:11:50,807 --> 01:11:52,408
I'll come back again later.

1520
01:11:52,408 --> 01:11:53,709
- You'll come back?
- Yes.

1521
01:11:53,709 --> 01:11:54,677
But where is everyone?

1522
01:11:54,677 --> 01:11:56,279
Is there a rumor
that our desserts are bad?

1523
01:11:56,279 --> 01:11:57,747
Why is no one coming?

1524
01:11:57,747 --> 01:11:59,148
Everyone's been raving about it.

1525
01:11:59,148 --> 01:12:01,551
- Then why is it so quiet?
- It's the countryside.

1526
01:12:01,551 --> 01:12:02,618
Is that why?

1527
01:12:02,618 --> 01:12:03,519
Yes.

1528
01:12:03,519 --> 01:12:05,221
[Cheering Up A Downhearted Barista]
We were so busy last week.

1529
01:12:05,221 --> 01:12:06,889
Your desserts are really tasty.

1530
01:12:06,889 --> 01:12:08,457
- I'll come by to buy some more later.
- Okay.

1531
01:12:08,457 --> 01:12:10,759
I'm upset that not many people came by.

1532
01:12:13,763 --> 01:12:15,198
- Enjoy the kimchi.
- We will!

1533
01:12:15,198 --> 01:12:16,265
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1534
01:12:16,265 --> 01:12:18,601
- Thank you.
- We'll enjoy it.

1535
01:12:18,601 --> 01:12:20,536
- See you later.
- Okay, I'm off to the Village Hall.

1536
01:12:20,536 --> 01:12:21,671
Are you?

1537
01:12:21,671 --> 01:12:23,673
Can you tell people we're waiting?

1538
01:12:23,673 --> 01:12:25,007
- I will.
- Thank you.

1539
01:12:28,010 --> 01:12:30,312
[Kimchi From The Senior Lady
Who Lives Next Door]

1540
01:12:30,880 --> 01:12:34,316
[Stored Safely In Chef Cha's Treasure]

1541
01:12:35,251 --> 01:12:38,054
It's so quiet.

1542
01:12:38,054 --> 01:12:39,388
I was so nervous

1543
01:12:39,388 --> 01:12:41,991
that I practiced at a friend's cafè.

1544
01:12:41,991 --> 01:12:43,559
[Recounting Tales]
At the start,

1545
01:12:43,559 --> 01:12:46,596
[In Front Of A New Part-Timer]
it was busy, and I was still learning.

1546
01:12:46,596 --> 01:12:49,599
I didn't expect it to get this quiet.

1547
01:12:49,599 --> 01:12:52,101
I feel so awkward as a part-time newbie.

1548
01:12:52,101 --> 01:12:53,502
I don't know what to do with myself.

1549
01:12:53,502 --> 01:12:56,772
[Typical Newbie Behavior]
[It's Awkward To Just Stand Around]

1550
01:13:00,877 --> 01:13:03,546
[Typical Newbie Behavior]
[Sweeping The Counter Just To Keep Busy]

1551
01:13:06,749 --> 01:13:08,651
[Awkward Laugh]

1552
01:13:08,651 --> 01:13:10,353
- I feel so awkward.
- Right?

1553
01:13:10,353 --> 01:13:11,821
I can see you brushing away the coffee...

1554
01:13:11,821 --> 01:13:12,822
What do I do?

1555
01:13:12,822 --> 01:13:14,624
What should I do? I can't keep still.

1556
01:13:14,624 --> 01:13:16,592
Should we do Sudoku or something?

1557
01:13:17,426 --> 01:13:19,428
[Practicing Preparing The Drinks]

1558
01:13:19,428 --> 01:13:20,997
What are you making?

1559
01:13:20,997 --> 01:13:22,665
- The lemon honey tea.
- But...

1560
01:13:22,665 --> 01:13:25,167
You need to... Hang on.

1561
01:13:25,167 --> 01:13:26,669
- Should I try again?
- You shouldn't use that.

1562
01:13:26,669 --> 01:13:27,870
[One-On-One Training By The Manager]

1563
01:13:27,870 --> 01:13:29,972
Hold on. You should use this instead.

1564
01:13:29,972 --> 01:13:32,208
Here. Hang on.

1565
01:13:32,208 --> 01:13:34,777
[Even After The Drink Lesson]
It's ready now.

1566
01:13:35,411 --> 01:13:40,182
[There Are Still No Customers]

1567
01:13:40,182 --> 01:13:43,352
I feel like someone's
interfering with our business.

1568
01:13:43,352 --> 01:13:44,253
[Sudden Conspiracy Theory]

1569
01:13:44,253 --> 01:13:46,355
I think we have competition.

1570
01:13:46,355 --> 01:13:50,927
[Crunch]
Another bakery is trying to drag us down.

1571
01:13:50,927 --> 01:13:52,962
It's unacceptable.

1572
01:13:53,963 --> 01:13:55,598
Why isn't anyone coming?

1573
01:13:56,198 --> 01:13:57,934
What's going on?

1574
01:13:57,934 --> 01:13:59,201
Is it because of me?

1575
01:13:59,201 --> 01:14:02,338
We even have extra hands on deck today.

1576
01:14:02,939 --> 01:14:06,142
I had a bad feeling about Joo Bin coming.

1577
01:14:06,142 --> 01:14:07,443
I had a weird feeling.

1578
01:14:08,844 --> 01:14:11,314
Some people attract customers,

1579
01:14:11,314 --> 01:14:13,282
while others drive them away.

1580
01:14:13,816 --> 01:14:15,518
What are you on about?

1581
01:14:15,518 --> 01:14:16,786
Joo Bin is the latter.

1582
01:14:16,786 --> 01:14:20,122
Joo Bin is scaring away the customers.

1583
01:14:20,122 --> 01:14:22,858
[Another Typical Newbie Behavior]

1584
01:14:24,060 --> 01:14:25,928
[When Business Is Going Badly]

1585
01:14:25,928 --> 01:14:30,232
[It Feels Like You're Somehow Responsible]

1586
01:14:35,471 --> 01:14:37,840
[Nervous Gulp]

1587
01:14:38,741 --> 01:14:40,910
I see a senior lady.

1588
01:14:40,910 --> 01:14:44,213
[Hurrying Over]

1589
01:14:46,115 --> 01:14:47,450
She's with a senior gentleman!

1590
01:14:47,450 --> 01:14:49,251
There's a senior gentleman.

1591
01:14:50,219 --> 01:14:51,187
Ma'am.

1592
01:14:51,187 --> 01:14:53,122
[Run Joo Bin]
Ma'am!

1593
01:14:53,122 --> 01:14:55,491
Where are you going?

1594
01:14:55,491 --> 01:14:56,759
I'm on my way home.

1595
01:14:56,759 --> 01:14:58,561
You're heading home?

1596
01:14:58,561 --> 01:15:00,129
- Have you eaten?
- No.

1597
01:15:00,129 --> 01:15:02,431
You haven't eaten yet.

1598
01:15:03,065 --> 01:15:04,867
We serve lots of different types of bread.

1599
01:15:04,867 --> 01:15:06,635
We sell tea and many tasty treats.

1600
01:15:06,635 --> 01:15:08,270
Yeah, I heard.

1601
01:15:08,270 --> 01:15:09,672
Should I buy some bread to go?

1602
01:15:09,672 --> 01:15:11,640
Please do! Come on in.

1603
01:15:12,308 --> 01:15:13,876
Come with me.

1604
01:15:15,811 --> 01:15:17,513
[Let Me Park First]

1605
01:15:17,513 --> 01:15:19,048
[Sheepish Giggle]

1606
01:15:21,417 --> 01:15:23,085
Come on in, sir.

1607
01:15:23,085 --> 01:15:24,920
You should come.

1608
01:15:24,920 --> 01:15:27,123
[The Newbie Saves The Day!]

1609
01:15:27,123 --> 01:15:29,625
Welcome!

1610
01:15:30,659 --> 01:15:32,161
- Welcome!
- Welcome!

1611
01:15:32,161 --> 01:15:33,462
Hello, ma'am.

1612
01:15:33,462 --> 01:15:37,233
You're the best, Joo Bin.

1613
01:15:37,233 --> 01:15:38,334
Is that you, Seon Ho?

1614
01:15:38,334 --> 01:15:41,603
I'm back, Seung Won.

1615
01:15:44,140 --> 01:15:46,968
[You Did Great!]

1616
01:15:47,843 --> 01:15:49,879
How did it go today?

1617
01:15:49,879 --> 01:15:52,014
- How did you find it?
- For me...

1618
01:15:52,615 --> 01:15:55,551
Honestly, it was such a hectic day.

1619
01:15:55,551 --> 01:15:58,087
My mind was...

1620
01:15:58,087 --> 01:16:01,157
My mind was racing all day.

1621
01:16:01,157 --> 01:16:05,061
But I tried my best to put on a calm face.

1622
01:16:05,061 --> 01:16:06,729
That's the most important thing.

1623
01:16:06,729 --> 01:16:08,764
You taught me yesterday.

1624
01:16:08,764 --> 01:16:10,699
- But...
- Yes?

1625
01:16:10,699 --> 01:16:13,536
- He handled it well, right?
- He did well.

1626
01:16:13,536 --> 01:16:15,771
The day went smoothly.

1627
01:16:15,771 --> 01:16:18,107
To be honest, I did make a few mistakes.

1628
01:16:18,107 --> 01:16:20,109
[You Said It Went Smoothly]
What mistakes?

1629
01:16:20,109 --> 01:16:22,978
After I made the drinks,

1630
01:16:22,978 --> 01:16:23,979
I realized I messed up.

1631
01:16:23,979 --> 01:16:25,381
In what way?

1632
01:16:25,381 --> 01:16:27,349
Oh, you got the order wrong?

1633
01:16:27,349 --> 01:16:29,585
I added water to the vanilla latte.

1634
01:16:29,585 --> 01:16:30,486
[A Sympathetic Chuckle]

1635
01:16:30,486 --> 01:16:31,654
So what did you do?

1636
01:16:31,654 --> 01:16:32,667
But...

1637
01:16:32,667 --> 01:16:34,623
When one thing goes wrong,

1638
01:16:34,623 --> 01:16:38,567
all the drink orders get mixed up.

1639
01:16:38,567 --> 01:16:39,634
Right.

1640
01:16:39,634 --> 01:16:43,566
After I made the mistake,

1641
01:16:43,566 --> 01:16:45,568
[Mental Breakdown]
I stopped in my tracks.

1642
01:16:45,568 --> 01:16:46,902
I was so flustered at first.

1643
01:16:46,902 --> 01:16:49,805
Honestly, my hands started shaking.

1644
01:16:49,805 --> 01:16:50,973
I get that.

1645
01:16:50,973 --> 01:16:54,210
[It Turned Out Well In The End]
I stayed calm in the end and started over.

1646
01:16:54,210 --> 01:16:56,846
- You ended up starting over.
- Yes.

1647
01:16:56,846 --> 01:16:58,481
[But For Some Reason]

1648
01:16:58,481 --> 01:17:02,151
[It Feels Like A Good Night To Open Up]

1649
01:17:03,552 --> 01:17:07,556
[And Share His Feelings With The Guys]

1650
01:17:08,190 --> 01:17:10,359
Thank you.

1651
01:17:11,660 --> 01:17:13,028
Thanks a lot for helping.

1652
01:17:13,028 --> 01:17:14,897
Let's meet again.

1653
01:17:28,167 --> 01:17:29,678
[Thanks For Your Hard Work]

1654
01:17:29,678 --> 01:17:33,916
[Ong Seong Wu!]
